WEBVTT

00:06.000 --> 00:12.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

02:54.800 --> 02:55.800
...in case we miss the train
or something.

02:56.144 --> 02:57.965
We have the big place in
Yonkers. Of course, yes.

02:58.065 --> 02:59.642
What did he say?
He said, "Of course."

02:59.742 --> 03:01.306
We're from Texas originally.
Of course.

03:01.406 --> 03:03.165
What did he say?
He said, "Of course!"

03:03.265 --> 03:05.117
Why does he keep saying
the same thing all the time?

03:05.217 --> 03:06.940
My husband's a little deaf.
Of course, yes.

03:07.040 --> 03:08.017
What did he say?

03:08.117 --> 03:10.812
He said, "It's as quiet as a tomb
here." Just what we're looking for!

03:10.912 --> 03:13.467
I don't mind a little life.
We'll be dead soon enough.

03:13.567 --> 03:15.407
Come in.
Concrete.

03:15.889 --> 03:16.863
I said, "Come in!"

03:16.963 --> 03:18.717
I'm fine, thanks. How are you?

03:18.818 --> 03:20.639
I hope all the tenants
aren't as disagreeable.

03:20.739 --> 03:22.331
I can assure you they're not.

03:22.431 --> 03:24.838
The building is very friendly,
efficient, and quiet.

03:25.969 --> 03:27.003
She got in by mistake.

03:27.103 --> 03:28.479
But she's leaving the
first thing in the morning.

03:28.579 --> 03:29.552
What?

03:29.652 --> 03:31.324
I said, "She's leaving the
first thing in the morning."

03:31.424 --> 03:34.191
Who? My wife? Are you going
home to see your mother?

03:36.401 --> 03:39.134
What's that? Canary?
I love birds.

03:39.234 --> 03:41.146
I said, "She's leaving the
first thing in the morning."

03:41.246 --> 03:42.216
You don't have to shout

03:42.316 --> 03:43.934
and your best friend ought
to tell you a little secret.

03:44.034 --> 03:45.564
Just speak
in a low clear voice.

03:45.664 --> 03:47.643
I said, "She's leaving the
first thing in the morning."

03:47.743 --> 03:51.131
She got in by mistake,
but tomorrow, she flies away.

03:51.231 --> 03:54.120
I understand it's a bird.
What about it? I like birds.

03:54.482 --> 03:55.791
It's right here.

03:59.186 --> 04:00.187
Duplex.

04:00.287 --> 04:01.372
What's the ceiling
so high up for?

04:01.472 --> 04:02.972
Why, that's what duplex means.
One floor up over...

04:03.072 --> 04:04.701
You don't seem to keep
the apartment very clean.

04:04.801 --> 04:05.772
What's on the balcony?

04:05.872 --> 04:07.617
You see, the former tenants
aren't getting the service.

04:07.717 --> 04:09.984
A little delinquency
in the rent.

04:10.084 --> 04:12.094
What did he say? I don't
like him to talk to me.

04:12.194 --> 04:14.238
He says the former tenants
haven't been getting any service.

04:14.338 --> 04:16.992
That's why the place is so
dirty. They didn't pay the rent.

04:17.091 --> 04:19.361
I don't mind a little dirt.
That's the trouble with women.

04:19.461 --> 04:21.599
Always fussing around, looking
for something to pick on.

04:21.699 --> 04:22.717
You can
tell me later, Arthur.

04:22.817 --> 04:26.082
Never satisfied with things
the way the Lord made them.

04:26.182 --> 04:29.760
Why, dirt is as natural in
this world as sin, disease,

04:29.860 --> 04:33.161
storms, twisters,
floods, and cyclones.

06:05.753 --> 06:07.812
Is there anything else
you'd like to try?

06:07.912 --> 06:09.955
What you doing in the bathtub
with a wrapper on?

06:10.055 --> 06:12.451
I might ask you what
you're doing in my bathroom.

06:12.551 --> 06:15.336
I don't suppose you go with the
flat. No, that's too much to hope for.

06:15.436 --> 06:17.476
Thank you. I'm glad you
like my perfume, too.

06:17.576 --> 06:18.576
Huh?

06:20.026 --> 06:22.597
I said, "I'm glad
you like my perfume, too."

06:22.697 --> 06:25.188
You have a lovely,
clear voice like a bell.

06:25.288 --> 06:27.845
If I was married to you, I'd
hear everything you said almost,

06:27.945 --> 06:29.158
but you wouldn't enjoy it.

06:29.258 --> 06:31.049
Besides, I'm already married.

06:31.149 --> 06:32.970
So am I.
Me, too.

06:33.070 --> 06:35.224
Anyway,
I'd be too old for you.

06:35.580 --> 06:39.079
"Cold are the hands of time
that creep along relentlessly,

06:39.179 --> 06:43.304
"destroying slowly but without
pity that which yesterday was young.

06:43.404 --> 06:46.056
"Alone our memories
resist this disintegration

06:46.156 --> 06:48.923
"and grow more lovely
with the passing years."

06:49.596 --> 06:51.701
That's hard to say
with false teeth.

06:53.500 --> 06:55.338
You're a funny old man.

06:55.438 --> 06:58.650
I didn't get it, but you looked
very pretty when you said it.

06:58.845 --> 07:00.105
I love birds.

07:00.205 --> 07:01.320
You do?

07:01.420 --> 07:04.041
Say, if they're showing the
apartment and you're still in it,

07:04.141 --> 07:05.482
you must be broke?

07:05.582 --> 07:06.630
No, it doesn't matter.

07:06.730 --> 07:08.058
What did you say?

07:08.381 --> 07:11.162
Yes. That varmint renting
it out from under you?

07:11.262 --> 07:13.577
Yes.
I know how you feel.

07:13.677 --> 07:17.672
I was broke, too, when I was about your age,
but I didn't have a figure like you've got.

07:17.772 --> 07:20.555
I had to use my brains.
You'll get over it.

07:20.655 --> 07:22.378
You'll get over
being young, too.

07:22.478 --> 07:25.259
Someday, you'll wake up and
find everything behind you.

07:25.359 --> 07:26.758
Gives you quite a turn.

07:26.858 --> 07:30.603
Makes you sorry for a few of the things
you didn't do while you still could.

07:30.703 --> 07:31.816
Are you sorry?

07:31.916 --> 07:33.211
How much rent do you owe?

07:33.470 --> 07:34.919
Well, that isn't really
your business.

07:35.019 --> 07:37.046
I can't hear you.
You're mumbling.

07:37.150 --> 07:40.331
I said, "It isn't really
your business!"

07:40.431 --> 07:43.434
I'm in the sausage business.
Don't worry about me.

07:43.534 --> 07:45.000
This'll be a hot one
on the wife.

07:45.100 --> 07:47.626
She's down there poking her
snoot in everybody's business

07:47.726 --> 07:49.640
and egged on by that varmint.

07:49.740 --> 07:51.189
How much do you need?

07:52.032 --> 07:54.381
Don't be silly.
Will $500 cover it?

07:54.481 --> 07:55.723
Please don't talk nonsense.

07:55.823 --> 07:57.677
I can't hear you.
You're mumbling again.

07:57.777 --> 07:59.499
You shouldn't mumble
with such a lovely voice.

07:59.599 --> 08:01.356
I wouldn't do this
for everybody.

08:01.456 --> 08:03.147
Look, this joke
has gone far enough.

08:03.247 --> 08:05.322
You say that ain't enough?
Well, how much do you need?

08:05.422 --> 08:07.403
You're...
You're just embarrassing me.

08:07.503 --> 08:09.327
That's all right,
don't mention it.

08:09.427 --> 08:12.012
It's a privilege to do a favor
for such a beautiful lady.

08:12.112 --> 08:14.398
It makes me feel
young again. There!

08:15.137 --> 08:18.699
How do you suppose it makes me feel? I
haven't seen anything like this for so long.

08:18.799 --> 08:21.706
If you're talking about the money,
forget it. I'm cheesy with money.

08:21.806 --> 08:24.558
I'm the Wienie King.
Invented the Texas Wienie.

08:24.658 --> 08:26.648
Lay off them,
you'll live longer.

08:26.752 --> 08:30.477
Here! Buy yourself a new
dress, too, and a new hat.

08:30.577 --> 08:32.831
You're a fine girl. So long.

08:34.306 --> 08:36.160
Whoopee! Hot diggity!

08:42.881 --> 08:43.856
Hello.

08:43.956 --> 08:46.891
Give me Longacre 56599,
please.

08:46.991 --> 08:49.517
You see, it's strong and safe.
It's simple and practical.

08:49.617 --> 08:52.864
It lets the light and air through and
it's practically invisible from below.

08:53.955 --> 08:55.502
And it's built right in
the middle of the city

08:55.602 --> 08:57.996
instead of way out
in the sticks somewhere.

08:58.096 --> 09:00.898
Excuse me a moment.
Be right back.

09:02.500 --> 09:03.470
Yes?

09:03.570 --> 09:06.445
Darling, the most exciting
thing has happened.

09:06.545 --> 09:09.362
Look, honey, I'm right in the middle of
a talk with a very important gentleman.

09:09.462 --> 09:10.736
Could you tell me later?

09:10.836 --> 09:12.129
All right, dear.

09:15.300 --> 09:16.624
Of course,
this is the big one.

09:16.724 --> 09:19.597
But to build a working model in
some field or village somewhere

09:19.697 --> 09:21.424
that small planes
could actually land on

09:21.524 --> 09:25.266
to prove that it was practical,
would only cost about $99,000.

09:25.366 --> 09:27.171
After that, we'd be on velvet.

09:28.100 --> 09:31.404
You see, it's a steel mesh
made of stretched cables.

09:31.504 --> 09:33.777
Every municipality, every
town, every city needs one.

09:33.877 --> 09:34.927
My patent is basic.

09:35.027 --> 09:36.623
$99,000 is a lot of money.

09:36.723 --> 09:38.865
But it isn't what it costs,
it's what it brings you back.

09:38.965 --> 09:42.706
You see, I've got $99,000 now, but if
I was to build this thing, I might...

09:42.806 --> 09:45.491
Look, let's start all over
again from the beginning.

09:45.591 --> 09:47.503
Well, go ahead.
My time ain't worth anything.

09:47.603 --> 09:48.670
I'm retired.

09:56.741 --> 09:57.741
Psst!

09:59.335 --> 10:01.189
Hey, Mike, come here a minute.

10:03.431 --> 10:06.131
Take a gander inside, will you, and
see if the manager's gone to dinner?

10:06.231 --> 10:08.403
I don't want to see
him face-to-face. Sure.

10:08.503 --> 10:11.766
But if it's the rent you're thinking about,
you can go in and whistle up his nose.

10:11.866 --> 10:13.686
It's paid. It's paid? What
do you mean, "It's paid"?

10:13.786 --> 10:15.092
It's paid.
Who paid it?

10:15.192 --> 10:16.592
Your wife.
My wife?

10:16.692 --> 10:19.698
I'm sure it wasn't mine.
An old man gave her the money.

10:19.798 --> 10:20.775
An old man gave her the money?

10:20.875 --> 10:22.321
What do you mean, "An old
man gave her the money?"

10:22.421 --> 10:26.166
I said I'm taking you to dinner, and
then the theater, and then supper.

10:26.266 --> 10:28.371
So hurry up
and put on your dinner jacket.

10:28.471 --> 10:29.732
Just a minute.

10:29.928 --> 10:32.499
What's all this malarkey about
some old man paying the rent for you

10:32.599 --> 10:34.260
that the whole building
is buzzing with?

10:34.360 --> 10:36.084
It's not malarkey, darling.

10:36.184 --> 10:38.545
Here's the receipted bill.
You see, it says "paid."

10:38.645 --> 10:41.171
And I paid the butcher, and
the grocer, and the drugstore.

10:41.271 --> 10:42.867
And I got this dress,
and had my hair done,

10:42.967 --> 10:45.043
and six pairs of stockings,
and some new shoes.

10:45.143 --> 10:47.894
And here's $14 in change.
That's for you.

10:47.994 --> 10:49.717
Isn't it wonderful?
Sensational.

10:49.817 --> 10:51.443
But you haven't quite
answered my question yet.

10:51.543 --> 10:52.520
What question, dear?

10:52.620 --> 10:54.772
Why this alleged old man
gave you... How much is it?

10:54.872 --> 10:56.818
$700.
$700.

10:56.918 --> 10:58.662
Why?
No reason.

10:59.049 --> 11:02.165
Is that so? He just... $700
just like that? Just like that.

11:02.265 --> 11:03.958
I mean, sex didn't even
enter into it.

11:04.058 --> 11:06.581
Oh, but of course
it did, darling.

11:06.681 --> 11:09.652
I don't think he'd have given it
to me if I had hair like excelsior

11:09.752 --> 11:11.381
and little short legs
like an alligator.

11:11.481 --> 11:13.239
Sex always has something
to do with it, dear.

11:13.339 --> 11:15.251
I see. From the time you're about so big

11:15.351 --> 11:17.235
and wondering
why your girlfriends' fathers

11:17.335 --> 11:19.161
are getting so arch
all of a sudden.

11:19.261 --> 11:22.343
Nothing wrong, just an overture
to the opera that's coming.

11:23.468 --> 11:25.461
I see.
No, you don't really.

11:25.561 --> 11:27.957
But from then on, you get
it from cops, taxi drivers,

11:28.057 --> 11:29.816
bellboys,
delicatessen dealers...

11:29.916 --> 11:30.908
Got what?

11:31.008 --> 11:31.994
The look.

11:32.094 --> 11:34.166
You know, "How's about
this evening, babe?"

11:34.266 --> 11:35.862
So this gent
gave you the look.

11:35.962 --> 11:37.752
The Wienie King? Oh, no.

11:37.852 --> 11:40.536
At his age, darling,
it was really more of a blink.

11:40.636 --> 11:42.327
Really?
This is very illuminating.

11:42.427 --> 11:43.802
Well, you don't have to
get rigid about it.

11:43.902 --> 11:45.657
It was perfectly innocent,
I assure you.

11:45.757 --> 11:47.780
Where did you meet
this Wienie King?

11:48.205 --> 11:49.718
You'll die laughing
when you hear.

11:49.818 --> 11:51.365
All right. Convulse me.

11:52.972 --> 11:55.640
In the bathtub.
In the bathtub?

11:55.740 --> 11:57.464
Yes, isn't that charming?
Delicious.

11:57.564 --> 11:58.906
What were you doing
in the bathtub?

11:59.006 --> 12:00.917
I was hiding from him.
Hiding?

12:01.017 --> 12:03.224
What kind of games do you
play around here while I'm out?

12:03.324 --> 12:05.464
I wish you could have seen
the expression on his face.

12:05.564 --> 12:06.890
I'm glad I didn't.

12:07.086 --> 12:08.599
How much water was there
in the tub?

12:08.699 --> 12:10.523
I was standing
in the bathtub, foolish.

12:10.623 --> 12:12.216
You were standing
in the bathtub?

12:12.316 --> 12:13.895
In my pink wrapper.

12:14.382 --> 12:17.211
Darling, he was just a funny
little old man in a funny hat.

12:17.311 --> 12:19.643
He sat on the edge of the bed
and talked for a while.

12:19.743 --> 12:21.370
He's on the bed now, is he?

12:21.470 --> 12:23.513
There aren't any chairs
in the bedroom, darling.

12:23.613 --> 12:25.592
Well, what was he doing
in the bedroom?

12:25.692 --> 12:27.418
He wanted
to rent the apartment,

12:27.518 --> 12:31.099
but when he found out we were
broke, he gave me $700 and he left.

12:31.199 --> 12:32.427
Just like that.

12:32.624 --> 12:33.948
Well, I did kiss him goodbye.

12:34.048 --> 12:35.707
Now the truth is coming out.

12:35.807 --> 12:36.807
The...

12:37.360 --> 12:38.361
The truth.

12:38.461 --> 12:41.336
You just tell me where this Wienie King
lives and I'll take his money back to him

12:41.436 --> 12:43.832
and tell him what I think of it. I
don't know where he lives, darling.

12:43.932 --> 12:46.841
I don't even know his name and I
don't think they'd give the money back.

12:46.941 --> 12:48.953
I mean, the grocer
and the drugstore and all.

12:49.053 --> 12:51.388
You really couldn't blame them
after they waited so long.

12:51.488 --> 12:53.359
That's right. Rub it in.

13:02.000 --> 13:03.429
Tom.
Yes.

13:05.393 --> 13:08.011
It's wonderful to have
the rent paid, isn't it?

13:08.529 --> 13:11.496
And the bills settled up.
You feel free and clean,

13:12.208 --> 13:14.266
and I like that feeling. I
wish it were always like that.

13:14.366 --> 13:15.814
Don't you think I do?

13:16.144 --> 13:18.348
I'd almost forgotten
what it was like.

13:18.960 --> 13:23.069
I don't look forward to being in debt again
and slinking past everybody. I dread it.

13:23.169 --> 13:26.139
It isn't going to be for always.
Everybody's a flop until he's a success.

13:26.239 --> 13:28.575
Something's bound to come
through. I got too many good ideas.

13:28.675 --> 13:30.666
Say, there's
a $2 overcharge here.

13:31.539 --> 13:34.386
Now that everything's paid up,
you could move.

13:35.282 --> 13:37.137
Well, where'd we go?

13:38.066 --> 13:40.587
I wasn't thinking about me.
I just meant you.

13:41.779 --> 13:44.300
Oh. You mean the bust-up?

13:45.395 --> 13:46.395
Hmm-mmm.

13:47.508 --> 13:49.501
When did you get that idea?
This afternoon?

13:49.601 --> 13:52.288
I've had it for some time,
but something always said,

13:52.388 --> 13:55.519
"Wait till he crashes through,
wait till he's made one success."

13:55.619 --> 13:57.343
You'll never make a success
with me around.

13:57.443 --> 14:00.395
I'm just a milestone
around your neck. Millstone.

14:01.332 --> 14:02.526
I'm no good for you, darling.

14:02.626 --> 14:05.630
I don't mean I'm not good for
somebody, but I can't cook or sew

14:05.730 --> 14:08.066
or whip up a little dress out
of last year's window curtains.

14:08.166 --> 14:09.158
What difference
does that make?

14:09.258 --> 14:11.937
I'm just like a car that only
gives seven miles to the tankful,

14:12.037 --> 14:13.436
only, you haven't got
the tankful.

14:13.536 --> 14:15.892
Are you sure
you haven't got a tankful?

14:16.501 --> 14:18.397
You see, by yourself,
you could live so simply.

14:18.497 --> 14:21.185
I mean, just a little room anywhere
or maybe move in with your brother,

14:21.285 --> 14:23.262
or even use the couch
in your office.

14:23.362 --> 14:25.120
And you wouldn't keep
slipping back all the time.

14:25.220 --> 14:27.613
You could balance what you earned
and look the world in the eye

14:27.713 --> 14:29.279
and maybe even
get ahead a little.

14:29.379 --> 14:31.105
Thanks. And what would
you be doing?

14:31.205 --> 14:32.255
That's no problem.

14:32.355 --> 14:34.912
You can always find a good
provider if you really want one.

14:35.012 --> 14:38.016
He may not look like a movie star,
but... We'll get ahead someday.

14:38.116 --> 14:41.763
But I don't want it someday. I want
it now while I can still enjoy it.

14:41.863 --> 14:43.684
Anyway, men don't get smarter
as they grow older,

14:43.784 --> 14:45.183
they just lose their hair.

14:45.283 --> 14:46.336
Gerry...
But, I would.

14:46.436 --> 14:48.481
I'm very tired
of being broke, darling.

14:48.581 --> 14:51.234
And feeling so helpless
about having my hands tied.

14:51.334 --> 14:53.344
I could've helped you
so many times,

14:53.444 --> 14:56.164
but every time I tried to, you
tried to punch the man in the nose.

14:56.264 --> 14:57.604
Don't talk rot.

14:57.704 --> 14:59.908
How about that president
of the smelting company?

15:00.008 --> 15:00.977
That wolf.

15:01.077 --> 15:03.041
He's still the president
of a smelting company.

15:03.141 --> 15:04.834
And we might've been
in the smelting business now

15:04.934 --> 15:06.400
and paying our rent.
Lovely.

15:06.500 --> 15:08.384
He liked you very much
he said.

15:08.484 --> 15:10.724
The less I hear about that
hyena, the better I'll like it.

15:10.824 --> 15:12.132
But that's what's
so irritating.

15:12.232 --> 15:16.129
To know that I could get you someplace,
without doing any harm, either.

15:16.229 --> 15:19.618
You have no idea what a long-legged
gal can do without doing anything.

15:19.718 --> 15:22.885
And instead of that, I have to
watch you stamping around proudly.

15:22.985 --> 15:26.019
Like Sitting Bull in a new
blanket, breathing through your nose

15:26.119 --> 15:28.001
while we both starve to death.
Thanks.

15:28.101 --> 15:29.569
You don't have to keep saying
thanks all the time.

15:29.669 --> 15:30.640
I'm not being so nice.

15:30.740 --> 15:31.876
That's the first time
I've said it.

15:31.976 --> 15:33.732
If you want a divorce, you're
certainly entitled to it,

15:33.832 --> 15:35.265
but I don't know
where the money's coming from.

15:35.365 --> 15:36.677
The next husband
always pays for that.

15:36.777 --> 15:39.940
You have him all picked out,
have you? You're such a child.

15:40.040 --> 15:43.735
He doesn't happen to be in the sausage
business by any chance, does he?

15:43.897 --> 15:47.363
I may not even get married again.
I might become an adventuress.

15:47.463 --> 15:50.614
I can just see you starting
for China in a 26-foot sailboat.

15:50.905 --> 15:52.834
You're thinking
of an adventurer, dear.

15:52.934 --> 15:56.836
An adventuress never goes on anything
under 300 feet with a crew of 80.

15:56.936 --> 16:00.550
You just let me catch you on a 300-foot
yacht, or even a 200-foot yacht.

16:00.650 --> 16:03.301
At least I wouldn't have
to worry about the rent.

16:03.401 --> 16:06.021
I'm sorry.
Let's go and have some dinner.

16:06.121 --> 16:08.726
How can you think of food
at a moment like this?

16:08.924 --> 16:11.941
Because I'm a woman, maybe, and
a little more practical than you.

16:12.041 --> 16:15.396
Are you going to put on your dinner
jacket, or shall I take off my new dress?

16:15.496 --> 16:16.912
Is that a new dress?

16:19.931 --> 16:21.638
You'll always be
a sister to me, huh?

16:21.738 --> 16:24.132
I know it sounds stupid,
but I'm a rotten wife.

16:24.232 --> 16:27.464
I can't sew, I can't cook.
You certainly can't.

16:27.564 --> 16:29.060
But just because
I'm a useless wife

16:29.160 --> 16:31.466
doesn't mean I couldn't be very
valuable to you as a sister.

16:31.566 --> 16:33.353
But very valuable.

16:33.453 --> 16:35.542
I remember that pot roast
you tried.

16:36.028 --> 16:37.444
And all the boys
who want to go out with me

16:37.544 --> 16:39.850
would naturally have to be
in your good graces.

16:39.950 --> 16:41.349
Naturally. Or I wouldn't
go out with them.

16:41.449 --> 16:42.599
I'll say you wouldn't.

16:42.699 --> 16:44.457
They'll probably offer you
partnerships.

16:44.557 --> 16:46.982
In the smelting business.
In the... No.

16:47.082 --> 16:48.059
You could have your choice.

16:48.159 --> 16:50.501
I don't begin and end
with a smelter, you know.

16:50.601 --> 16:53.752
I refuse to understand what
you're talking about, Geraldine.

16:53.916 --> 16:55.495
They'd work you in on deals

16:55.595 --> 16:58.281
and let you in on all the good things
that were happening in the market

16:58.381 --> 17:00.391
and that kind of business.
Monkey business.

17:00.491 --> 17:03.739
Well, very few pretty girls'
brothers have ever failed, you know.

17:03.839 --> 17:06.188
If they knew enough
to come in out of a hailstorm.

17:06.288 --> 17:08.232
Well, in the first place, I
don't happen to be your brother.

17:08.332 --> 17:09.642
In the second place,
may I ask

17:09.742 --> 17:12.825
who are all these men who are
going to faint at your feet?

17:12.925 --> 17:15.114
You think there aren't any. I
didn't say there weren't any.

17:15.214 --> 17:16.296
I just said, "Where are they?"

17:16.396 --> 17:20.661
They're around. They're always there
and they make new ones every year.

17:20.767 --> 17:22.124
I don't want to be rude,
honey, but...

17:22.223 --> 17:24.104
You're not being rude, dear,
you're just being yourself.

17:24.204 --> 17:27.690
You see, you're married to me.
That's like saying you're blind to me.

17:27.790 --> 17:29.483
For a long time,
I've been a part of you,

17:29.583 --> 17:32.747
just something to snuggle up to and
keep you warm at night, like a blanket.

17:32.847 --> 17:35.661
But you can't see me any more than
you can see the back of your neck.

17:35.761 --> 17:37.995
I put on new dresses,
I change my hair...

17:38.095 --> 17:41.545
Would you mind not looking quite so
gorgeous while you say all these things?

17:41.645 --> 17:43.388
You're just plastered.
Yes.

17:43.488 --> 17:46.488
Well, I'd better get you home
before you fall apart.

17:47.488 --> 17:50.732
Or do you object to spending the
night under the same roof with me?

17:50.832 --> 17:52.823
I wasn't thinking
about the roof.

17:53.729 --> 17:54.729
Come on.

17:55.168 --> 17:57.339
Just a minute.
I gotta pay the check.

18:08.034 --> 18:10.092
I'll sleep on the thing here.

18:10.192 --> 18:11.917
You know we don't love
each other anymore.

18:12.017 --> 18:14.174
We're just habits. Bad habits.

18:15.778 --> 18:18.381
They don't make these zippers
as well as they used to.

18:18.481 --> 18:21.965
And when love's gone, there's nothing
left but admiration and respect.

18:22.065 --> 18:24.800
I think it's stuck. Will
you see if you can get it?

18:27.650 --> 18:29.505
Come around here in the light.

18:46.499 --> 18:47.993
Keep still, will you?

18:51.651 --> 18:54.368
You don't think this is
a little intimate, do you?

18:57.924 --> 19:00.781
Doesn't mean anything to
you anymore to sit on my lap?

19:00.881 --> 19:01.881
No.

19:02.149 --> 19:04.336
Or if I kiss you there?

19:04.436 --> 19:05.533
Stop it. No.

19:06.148 --> 19:07.148
Or here?

19:08.548 --> 19:09.726
It's nothing.

19:09.892 --> 19:10.892
Or here?

19:11.108 --> 19:13.005
You know I'm ticklish.

19:13.105 --> 19:14.671
Then why is
your breath coming faster?

19:14.771 --> 19:16.512
Because you're squeezing me.

19:21.925 --> 19:24.544
That doesn't mean anything
to you anymore, huh?

19:24.710 --> 19:25.954
Almost nothing.

19:26.407 --> 19:27.836
Almost nothing, huh?

19:39.335 --> 19:43.632
Almost nothing. Nothing
but a habit, a bad habit.

19:43.732 --> 19:44.799
It is, huh?

19:45.159 --> 19:47.697
Very, very bad, and wicked,

19:47.797 --> 19:50.354
and stupid, and useless,

19:50.454 --> 19:53.920
and young,
and impractical, and...

20:59.435 --> 21:01.174
Oh, darling!
What's the big idea?

21:01.274 --> 21:02.616
Darling, read the note.

21:02.716 --> 21:05.547
Goodbye. God bless you.
Take care of yourself.

21:14.315 --> 21:15.315
Hey!

21:39.244 --> 21:40.407
Hey, will you wait a minute?

21:40.507 --> 21:42.071
No, I won't.
I've made up my mind.

21:42.171 --> 21:43.352
It's best for both of us

21:43.452 --> 21:45.496
while we're still young enough
to make other connections.

21:45.596 --> 21:46.998
But you're forgetting
a little thing called love.

21:47.098 --> 21:49.209
Honey, I love you and you love
me. That's all that matters.

21:49.309 --> 21:52.229
That's all you can take with
you. Everything else is...

21:52.494 --> 21:54.903
I'm so sorry. Please
accept all my apologies.

21:55.003 --> 21:56.003
Gerry!

22:21.455 --> 22:22.633
Hey, Officer!

22:24.303 --> 22:26.776
Hold that woman!
She stole my suitcase!

22:26.876 --> 22:28.172
Why, you lying...

22:29.999 --> 22:31.342
You mean this one?

22:31.984 --> 22:33.991
That's right!
I'll be right down.

22:36.208 --> 22:38.746
Do I look like
a suitcase stealer to you?

22:38.846 --> 22:42.443
It isn't how you look, it's how you
behave that counts in this world.

22:44.432 --> 22:46.425
Now, I mind the time...
Oh, wise guy.

22:46.525 --> 22:47.961
Thanks for holding her,
Officer.

22:48.061 --> 22:50.268
You want to prepare charges or
something disagreeable like that?

22:50.368 --> 22:53.209
No, I prefer not to. This is my
wife. Mrs. Jeffers, Mr. Mulligan.

22:53.309 --> 22:55.771
The name happens to be O'Donnell,
if it's all the same to you.

22:55.871 --> 22:57.403
And I've a good mind to
charge you with false arrest,

22:57.503 --> 22:58.783
only, I don't know
if I could make it stick.

22:58.883 --> 23:00.126
Why don't you try?

23:00.226 --> 23:02.203
It's too nice a morning.
The heck with it.

23:02.303 --> 23:05.290
Why don't you two learn to
get along together? I had to.

23:05.746 --> 23:06.730
Now what?

23:06.830 --> 23:08.315
Now, will you come back
upstairs and be sensible?

23:08.415 --> 23:10.460
No, I won't!
Give me back my suitcase!

23:10.560 --> 23:13.375
It was hard enough to make up my
mind to do what I know is right.

23:13.475 --> 23:15.516
If I don't do it now, I'll
never be strong enough again.

23:15.616 --> 23:16.668
Now give me my suitcase.

23:16.768 --> 23:18.592
Stop talking like a fool,
Gerry. Where are you going?

23:18.692 --> 23:20.092
To visit your sister
in Long Island? Taxi!

23:20.192 --> 23:21.595
No, I'm going
to get a divorce.

23:21.695 --> 23:22.975
How can you get a divorce
without any money?

23:23.075 --> 23:25.084
How can you go any place?
Why don't you be sensible?

23:25.184 --> 23:26.269
You've just got a hangover.

23:26.369 --> 23:28.510
I don't need any money.
I've already told you.

23:28.610 --> 23:29.610
Taxi!

23:31.859 --> 23:33.853
Yes, ma'am? Where's the
best place to get a divorce?

23:33.953 --> 23:35.296
Gerry, for heaven's sake!

23:35.396 --> 23:37.981
Well, most people go to Reno, Nevada,
but for my money, it's Palm Beach.

23:38.081 --> 23:39.229
This time of the year,
you got the track,

23:39.329 --> 23:41.185
you got the ocean, you got
palm trees, three months.

23:41.285 --> 23:42.254
You leave from Penn Station.

23:42.354 --> 23:43.358
Look, I'm in awful trouble.

23:43.458 --> 23:45.437
I haven't got a dime. Would
you take me there for nothing?

23:45.537 --> 23:46.557
To where? Palm Beach?

23:46.657 --> 23:48.400
No, no. Just to the station.

23:48.820 --> 23:50.144
Sure. Hop in, babe.
Thanks!

23:50.244 --> 23:51.741
Listen, you!
Listen what?

23:51.841 --> 23:54.113
Will you give me my suitcase?
Give the lady her suitcase.

23:54.213 --> 23:55.309
Listen, you!

23:55.636 --> 23:57.985
Now look what you've done!
Look what I've done?

23:58.085 --> 23:59.824
Yeah. Look what you've done!

24:01.908 --> 24:02.908
Hey!

24:03.507 --> 24:05.362
What's the trouble now?
Taxi!

24:05.588 --> 24:07.412
Pick this stuff up, will you?

24:07.766 --> 24:08.813
Hey, you...

24:20.086 --> 24:21.086
Gerry!

24:23.222 --> 24:25.727
Gerry. Gerry, why, stop behaving
like a chicken with its head cut off.

24:25.827 --> 24:26.804
You haven't got any money.

24:26.904 --> 24:28.578
Where can you go?
I got this far, didn't I?

24:28.678 --> 24:29.954
But, Gerry...
Where's my suitcase?

24:30.054 --> 24:31.697
But, listen, honey.
Goodbye.

24:35.223 --> 24:37.379
Listen to me, you're making a fool out
of yourself, right in front of all...

24:37.479 --> 24:39.424
Officer, this man is trying to
molest me. Will you stop him?

24:39.524 --> 24:41.283
Where you going in such a
hurry, laddy? Thank you so much.

24:41.383 --> 24:43.872
Now, you let the dames alone
at Pennsylvania Station,

24:43.972 --> 24:46.049
Pennsylvania Station will
leave you alone and vice versa.

24:46.149 --> 24:47.492
That's my wife,
you dumb cluck!

24:47.592 --> 24:49.120
So now I'm a dumb cluck, am I?

24:49.220 --> 24:51.778
I like peace,
but I ain't morbid about it.

24:51.878 --> 24:54.530
Now, stop annoying these Janes
or I'll lock you up!

24:54.630 --> 24:55.973
Attention, please.

24:56.073 --> 25:01.222
Last call. Atlantic Coast Line,
Florida Special, Advance Section

25:01.322 --> 25:04.599
leaving from Gate 12
in five minutes.

25:04.920 --> 25:06.562
Attention, please.

25:06.662 --> 25:09.892
Miami Special, due 11:21,
Track 3,

25:09.992 --> 25:11.748
arriving 12:04.

25:11.848 --> 25:14.337
Track 6 from Rockingham,
Burns,

25:14.437 --> 25:16.978
Charleston Springs,
and Saratoga.

25:19.674 --> 25:20.966
Pratt, Ale and Quail.
Pratt.

25:21.066 --> 25:22.773
Billdocker.
Billdocker.

25:23.226 --> 25:24.753
Hitchcock.
Hitchcock.

25:25.306 --> 25:26.353
Hotchkiss.

25:27.386 --> 25:30.437
I see we got the club
again, Ed. You're telling me.

25:30.537 --> 25:33.411
Just let them try and
start something. Hot dog.

25:33.511 --> 25:34.505
Is anything the matter, lady?

25:34.605 --> 25:37.124
I'll be all right. I'm sure
they'll come with my ticket.

25:37.224 --> 25:38.852
Did somebody forget
your ticket?

25:38.952 --> 25:41.735
I'm sure it'll be all right. It's
just that I have to get to Palm Beach.

25:41.835 --> 25:43.859
That's too bad. Dr. Kluck.

25:44.411 --> 25:46.853
I'm sure they'll come.
I beg your pardon.

25:46.953 --> 25:49.445
I'm sorry.
I was talking to the gateman.

25:49.545 --> 25:50.564
McKeewie.
McKeewie.

25:50.664 --> 25:52.935
I'm sure my ticket will come.
It must come.

25:53.035 --> 25:55.621
Oh, yes, it must.
By all means.

25:55.721 --> 25:57.512
Asweld. You say your ticket
didn't come yet?

25:57.612 --> 26:00.912
You haven't got much time. No,
but it'll be here. I'm sure.

26:01.819 --> 26:04.688
If there's anything
I can do... Thank you.

26:05.338 --> 26:07.511
Name, please. Go ahead.

26:08.444 --> 26:09.893
Hinch and valet.
Hinch.

26:09.993 --> 26:11.493
I'm sure it'll be all right.

26:11.593 --> 26:12.996
Is there something the matter,
madam?

26:13.096 --> 26:15.622
Nothing that anyone
can help me with, I'm afraid.

26:15.722 --> 26:18.375
It just looks as if my ticket
isn't going to get here on time.

26:18.475 --> 26:21.689
My gracious! There ought to be
some solution to that problem.

26:22.044 --> 26:23.767
I can't think of any.

26:24.316 --> 26:25.428
My gracious.

26:25.564 --> 26:27.369
No ticket?
No ticket.

26:27.469 --> 26:28.810
Jones.
Jones.

26:28.910 --> 26:30.965
Featherwax.
Featherwax.

26:31.293 --> 26:32.668
Attention, please.

26:33.277 --> 26:37.620
Florida Mail leaving through
Gate 9 at 11:57.

26:38.206 --> 26:41.322
Newark, Trenton,
North Philadelphia,

26:41.422 --> 26:44.755
Philadelphia, Baltimore,
Washington...

26:45.309 --> 26:47.303
You'd think one of them
would offer a lady a ticket.

26:47.403 --> 26:48.806
Oh, well, I couldn't
accept it.

26:48.906 --> 26:50.901
Why not? Rich millionaires?

26:51.934 --> 26:54.439
I have a feeling that
everything's gonna be all right.

26:54.539 --> 26:55.956
Aye!
Aye!

27:02.367 --> 27:03.815
Did it come yet?
No, but it's all right.

27:03.915 --> 27:05.513
What'd you mean it's all
right? It's far from all right.

27:05.613 --> 27:07.689
You see, we have a wonderful idea.
The other members and myself...

27:07.789 --> 27:09.514
You see, we have a private
car. We have tons of tickets.

27:09.614 --> 27:11.495
I could never accept. We're
just going to Savannah...

27:11.595 --> 27:12.972
But if you want to go
any further, we'd gladly...

27:13.072 --> 27:15.210
You can be our mascot.
You must be our mascot.

27:15.310 --> 27:17.515
Do you think it's all right?
All right? It's perfect.

27:17.615 --> 27:19.209
Then thank you
for your chivalry, gentlemen.

27:19.309 --> 27:21.451
I accept with pleasure.
The pleasure is ours.

27:21.551 --> 27:23.081
This is Asweld
of the American Asweldocan.

27:23.181 --> 27:24.940
Mr. Hinch. You've heard of
Hinch's Emulsion, I presume?

27:25.040 --> 27:26.413
And I am McKeewie
of the Seventh National.

27:26.513 --> 27:28.521
And I am Mrs. Thomas Jeffers,
alias Geraldine.

27:28.621 --> 27:29.867
Geraldine!

27:29.967 --> 27:31.276
And thank you
for your chivalry.

27:31.376 --> 27:33.002
Anytime from 8:00 to 12:00.

27:33.102 --> 27:34.103
Gerry!

27:34.496 --> 27:35.740
Goodbye, dear.

27:39.137 --> 27:40.493
Let me through there!
You got a ticket?

27:40.593 --> 27:42.025
Hey!
No ticket, no passing.

27:42.125 --> 27:43.243
Now, listen!

27:43.343 --> 27:45.102
All aboard!

27:45.202 --> 27:47.193
Gerry! Gerry!

28:44.867 --> 28:46.940
Hi. Come on in.
Oh, hello.

28:47.524 --> 28:49.394
Glad you... Glad you could come. Here!

28:49.494 --> 28:51.600
Not while we're on duty,
thanks. Who's the headman here?

28:51.700 --> 28:53.230
You mean the president
of the club?

28:53.330 --> 28:54.766
Whoever has the tickets,
we don't care.

28:54.866 --> 28:56.610
Oh, Ozzie! Front and center!

28:58.374 --> 29:00.691
There's Mr. Osmond, President
of the Ale and Quail Club.

29:00.791 --> 29:02.767
How are you?
It's about the tickets.

29:02.867 --> 29:05.683
How many in the party?
How many members in this club?

29:05.783 --> 29:10.501
Well, there's... There's...
There's Ozzie and Hitchie,

29:11.078 --> 29:12.402
and him, and him.

29:12.502 --> 29:14.770
That makes four. And you
and me, that makes six.

29:14.870 --> 29:16.977
I'm not a member of
this club. And why not?

29:17.077 --> 29:18.769
It isn't good enough
for you, eh?

29:18.869 --> 29:20.946
Now, let's get this straight.
How many members are there?

29:21.046 --> 29:23.154
One, two, three,
four, five, six. Six!

29:23.254 --> 29:25.362
All right, that's three.
Now, we'll start from there.

29:25.462 --> 29:26.895
You trying to make
a liar out of me?

29:26.995 --> 29:31.188
Mr. President, I move
that this member be expelled.

29:31.288 --> 29:33.777
Second the motion.
All those in favor say aye.

29:33.877 --> 29:35.456
Aye!
Aye!

29:36.231 --> 29:37.647
All right, we're expelled.

29:37.747 --> 29:39.825
Have a drink, boys.
Hey, that's four.

29:39.925 --> 29:42.961
That's seven. One, two,
three, four, five, six, seven.

29:43.061 --> 29:44.528
What's the matter with you?
You cockeyed?

29:44.628 --> 29:47.473
It ain't me that's cockeyed.
Looking for trouble, eh?

29:47.573 --> 29:50.593
Mr. Osmond doesn't always
carry his liquor to perfection.

29:53.031 --> 29:55.732
Now, let's start this all over.
Now, just a moment, Officer.

29:55.832 --> 29:58.565
I'm not an officer. I'm
the conductor on this train.

29:58.952 --> 30:01.491
All in flavor say aye.
- Aye!

30:01.591 --> 30:03.025
Opposed?
- Nay!

30:03.125 --> 30:05.666
Opposition vote.
- No!

30:11.946 --> 30:12.947
Good night.
Good night.

30:13.047 --> 30:14.903
If there's the slightest
trouble, just knock on my wall.

30:15.003 --> 30:16.882
Thank you, Mr...
Don't give it a thought.

30:16.982 --> 30:20.182
As I have so often said at dinners
and our little gatherings...

30:20.282 --> 30:21.844
Where's your baggage?
My... What?

30:21.944 --> 30:23.987
Where's your luggage? What
are you going to sleep in?

30:24.087 --> 30:25.398
That's quite all right.
I'll just...

30:25.498 --> 30:26.995
You see, I left so hurriedly.

30:27.095 --> 30:28.853
Why, bless my soul!
You stay right here.

30:28.953 --> 30:30.326
I'll have you a pair of
pajamas before you can say...

30:30.426 --> 30:31.402
What size do you take?

30:31.502 --> 30:35.177
Never mind. You'll have to take my size.
They maybe a little bit big, but still...

30:36.907 --> 30:39.256
...turning ever

30:39.356 --> 30:43.233
That's where
the old folks stay

30:44.426 --> 30:49.926
All the world
is sad and dreary

30:50.026 --> 30:53.287
Everywhere I roam

30:55.082 --> 31:01.624
Oh, darkies,
how my heart grows weary

31:01.724 --> 31:05.963
Far from the old folks at home

31:14.957 --> 31:16.004
Any calls?

31:35.341 --> 31:37.561
Hello, there. Where's that
pretty girl with the nice figure

31:37.661 --> 31:39.126
that lives here
that I seen yesterday?

31:39.226 --> 31:41.655
Who are you?
I'm fine, thanks. How are you?

31:41.755 --> 31:43.099
You must be her husband.
Where is she?

31:43.199 --> 31:45.208
What's that to your business?
I'm in the sausage business.

31:45.308 --> 31:47.223
Just wanted to tell her
we moved in after all.

31:47.323 --> 31:50.296
Took the green apartment down the hall
that the opera singer moved out of.

31:50.396 --> 31:51.373
She's gone.

31:51.473 --> 31:54.327
I say she's gone! She's gone to
Florida. She's going to divorce me.

31:54.427 --> 31:55.895
You say she's gone?
That's right.

31:55.995 --> 31:58.553
Good for her. A pretty girl
like that can get anybody.

31:58.653 --> 32:01.112
Why hang around with a man
that can't pay the rent?

32:01.212 --> 32:02.938
Look here, you old rattlebrain.
You've made trouble enough

32:03.038 --> 32:05.690
without getting insulting about it.
Don't you threaten me, you big baboon.

32:05.790 --> 32:08.858
I'm twice your age and only half as big,
but I'm mighty handy with this cane...

32:08.958 --> 32:11.034
All right, I'm sorry. I guess
you didn't mean any harm.

32:11.134 --> 32:13.159
You're probably
very kind at that.

32:14.832 --> 32:16.889
You say she's gone and
left you? That's right.

32:16.989 --> 32:18.521
How did she go? By train?

32:18.621 --> 32:19.900
That's right. That's right!

32:20.000 --> 32:22.393
Why don't you fly down there
in an aerioplane

32:22.493 --> 32:23.773
with a bunch of roses
in your hand

32:23.873 --> 32:25.785
and meet her when she gets off
and bring her home?

32:25.885 --> 32:27.353
Because I'm not
in the sausage business!

32:27.453 --> 32:30.971
So am I. And it's a good business if
you know where to get the meat cheap.

32:31.071 --> 32:34.076
That's my secret
and I ain't telling no one.

