and my shoes, and my makeup,

43:04.002 --> 43:06.241
my toothbrush.
Only, I don't think I had one.

43:06.341 --> 43:07.584
This is disgraceful.
I'll certainly write

43:07.684 --> 43:08.830
to the president
of the company.

43:08.930 --> 43:11.168
How could such a thing happen?
I don't know.

43:11.268 --> 43:14.464
My things seem to have gotten into
a car back there somewhere, somehow,

43:14.564 --> 43:16.509
and now the car
just doesn't seem to be there.

43:16.609 --> 43:18.848
Not that car full of drunks I
hope that they had to disconnect?

43:18.948 --> 43:20.063
Oh, perish the thought.

43:20.163 --> 43:23.232
Well, as soon as we come to a town, I
could jump over to a store and jump back.

43:23.332 --> 43:25.791
With a Mother Hubbard.
Well, that's very kind of you.

43:25.891 --> 43:28.480
In the meantime, I suppose I'll
have to lie here in this hatrack.

43:28.580 --> 43:31.583
Anyway, I haven't any money for you
to jump over to a store and back with.

43:31.683 --> 43:32.767
Oh, I have money.

43:32.867 --> 43:33.983
Oh, you have?
Oh, yes.

43:34.083 --> 43:36.833
Now, if you could just get over to
the store to pick out what you need...

43:36.933 --> 43:38.592
We got a stretcher
in the baggage car up ahead.

43:38.692 --> 43:41.824
Wouldn't that be stretching
it a little? Wait a minute.

43:41.924 --> 43:44.960
Maybe we could borrow some odd pieces
here and there among the lady passengers.

43:45.060 --> 43:46.273
Oh, murder.
That's a wonderful idea.

43:46.373 --> 43:48.286
You take that side and I'll
take this side. Yes, sir.

43:48.386 --> 43:49.934
And I'll take the neck.

43:58.742 --> 44:00.767
Here, we've got some more,
or are you satisfied?

44:00.867 --> 44:02.282
Satisfied?

44:07.574 --> 44:09.681
I could lend you
my earrings.

44:18.231 --> 44:20.053
Good morning.
Good morning.

44:24.792 --> 44:27.713
Oh, why, that's lovely. Now
you won't need anything else.

44:27.813 --> 44:29.556
That's what you think.

44:33.913 --> 44:35.075
Yes, ma'am.

44:35.175 --> 44:38.626
If there's one thing I admire, it's a woman
who can whip up something out of nothing.

44:38.726 --> 44:40.258
You should taste my popovers.

44:40.358 --> 44:41.475
I'd love to.

44:41.575 --> 44:43.716
The homely virtues are so
hard to find these days.

44:43.816 --> 44:47.202
A woman who can sew and cook and bake,
even if she doesn't have to, and knit and...

44:47.302 --> 44:49.060
And weave.
You're joking.

44:49.160 --> 44:51.521
But I mean, seriously,
that is a woman.

44:51.621 --> 44:52.933
Were you going to buy me
some breakfast,

44:53.033 --> 44:55.490
or would you like me to bake you
something right here at the table?

44:55.590 --> 44:58.425
I like a witty woman, too.
Now, what will you have?

44:58.553 --> 45:00.773
The 35-cent breakfast seems
the best at first glance,

45:00.873 --> 45:03.843
but if you analyze it for solid
value, the 55-cent is the one.

45:03.943 --> 45:05.891
Well, I wouldn't want
to impose.

45:05.991 --> 45:07.490
No, feel free
to choose anything you like.

45:07.590 --> 45:09.862
There's even a 75-cent
breakfast if it appeals to you.

45:09.962 --> 45:12.355
We might share one.
Wait a minute.

45:12.455 --> 45:14.532
With two eggs, toast,
and choice of fruit thrown in,

45:14.632 --> 45:18.052
I'm not sure the 75-cent breakfast
isn't the best value after all.

45:18.152 --> 45:19.269
Do we dare?

45:19.369 --> 45:21.829
I'm not really the way you think
I am. It's just my upbringing.

45:21.929 --> 45:23.305
Oh, waiter.
Yes, sir.

45:23.405 --> 45:25.160
Two 75-cent breakfasts,
please.

45:25.260 --> 45:27.879
I'll start with a prairie
oyster. Yes, ma'am.

45:27.979 --> 45:30.183
It's a very tempting choice
in the $1.10 breakfast.

45:30.283 --> 45:31.560
Two 75-cent breakfasts,

45:31.660 --> 45:33.767
