48:15.090 --> 48:16.914
They are all the rage.

48:17.014 --> 48:18.736
Why not? What kind
of stones do you like?

48:18.836 --> 48:21.668
Well...
Red. That is all the rage.

48:21.988 --> 48:23.437
You mean like garnets?

48:23.537 --> 48:26.372
Don't you think garnets
are a little lifeless?

48:30.628 --> 48:32.849
Why, certainly,
this is great fun.

48:32.949 --> 48:35.822
I've never bought things for a girl
before. I mean, in any such quantities.

48:35.922 --> 48:39.804
You've been denying yourself, monsieur,
one of the basic pleasures in life.

48:39.973 --> 48:41.402
I guess I have.

48:44.102 --> 48:45.744
All right.
Plus tax.

48:45.844 --> 48:47.790
Yes, it's these taxes
that get you down.

48:47.890 --> 48:49.747
I keep feeling that two
men with butterfly nets

48:49.847 --> 48:52.336
are going to creep up
behind you and lead you away.

48:52.436 --> 48:53.650
You're thinking of my uncle.

48:53.750 --> 48:56.144
I'm not the crazy one in the
family. I'm perfectly normal.

48:56.244 --> 48:58.640
Then why do you travel around
in a lower berth?

48:58.740 --> 49:00.306
I find it a little stuffy
in an upper.

49:00.406 --> 49:02.385
Oh, you mean why don't
I take a stateroom? Yes.

49:02.485 --> 49:04.195
Staterooms are un-American.

49:05.128 --> 49:07.957
Well, thank you.
Don't mention it.

49:08.057 --> 49:10.706
And now, if you can't think of
anything else, we'd better get started.

49:10.806 --> 49:11.783
Just charge everything,
please,

49:11.883 --> 49:14.099
and have it put in the
taxi. Good day. Excuse me.

49:14.199 --> 49:15.794
Oh, I'm so sorry. Forgive me.

49:15.894 --> 49:17.522
I'm so used to buying
in stores where I'm known

49:17.622 --> 49:18.868
that it totally
slipped my mind.

49:18.968 --> 49:22.100
Mr... That's all
right, don't mention it.

49:22.200 --> 49:24.275
Excuse me, please, that
I didn't... Good day.

49:24.375 --> 49:26.802
Well, what are you
standing there for?

49:26.902 --> 49:29.906
Where are the packages?
How about some service?

49:30.006 --> 49:33.604
Why do I got to do
everything myself?

49:44.234 --> 49:46.195
Is this yours?
Oh, yes.

49:46.295 --> 49:48.307
Actually, it was my grandfather's,
but he didn't like it.

49:48.407 --> 49:50.710
He only used it once.
This was his hat.

49:50.810 --> 49:53.014
Do you happen to remember how
much tip I gave the taxi driver?

49:53.114 --> 49:57.538
Well, I didn't see the coin, but from
his face, I think it was 10 cents.

49:57.770 --> 49:59.593
Tipping is un-American.

50:01.611 --> 50:03.945
What's your name?
Hackensacker.

50:05.130 --> 50:06.968
Not John D. Hackensacker?

50:07.068 --> 50:11.030
Oh, I'm not my grandfather, of course.
He's dead, anyway. I'm John D. The Third.

50:11.130 --> 50:13.270
Well, then, you're one of
the richest men in the world.

50:13.370 --> 50:15.046
Well, yes, I suppose so.

50:15.147 --> 50:17.205
I would step on your face.

50:17.305 --> 50:18.837
That's quite all right.
I rather enjoyed it.

50:18.937 --> 50:21.509
Twice.
You made quite an impression.

50:22.059 --> 50:24.279
May I get you a rug, madam?
Oh, no, thank you.

50:24.379 --> 50:27.479
Will you dine on deck, Mr.
Hackensacker, or in the saloon?

50:27.579 --> 50:30.900
We can have it on deck if you like, but
it blows everything all over the place.

50:31.000 --> 50:32.793
There are a lot of
inconveniences to yachting

50:32.893 --> 50:34.486
that most people
don't know anything about.

50:34.586 --> 50:36.280
Give me the peaceful train.

50:36.380 --> 50:37.754
In the saloon, please.

50:37.854 --> 50:38.949
Very good, madam.

50:40.652 --> 50:41.814
You see what I mean?

50:41.914 --> 50:44.023
I just happen to own this
thing or I'd never go near it.

50:44.123 --> 50:46.425
Did you say you were John
D. The Third or the Fourth?

50:46.525 --> 50:49.029
The Third. The Fourth will
be my son when I marry.

50:50.221 --> 50:53.719
Well, then it really didn't mean anything
to you to buy me all those things, did it?

50:53.819 --> 50:55.862
Well, I can't pretend
that it was a great sacrifice,

50:55.962 --> 50:57.527
but it did give me
a great deal of pleasure.

50:57.627 --> 50:59.352
You like to write
in your little book.

50:59.452 --> 51:00.600
It used to please
my grandfather.

51:00.700 --> 51:02.490
It's just a habit.
It's nonsense, really.

51:02.590 --> 51:04.696
I write things down,
but I never add them up.

51:04.796 --> 51:06.489
Where are you staying
in Palm Beach?

51:06.589 --> 51:08.428
Oh, no place yet.

51:08.749 --> 51:10.970
Where are you staying?
At my sister's.

51:11.070 --> 51:13.943
Oh, yes, the Princess.
Or is it the Duchess?

51:14.043 --> 51:15.258
The Princess Centimillia.

51:15.358 --> 51:16.837
Of course.

51:17.390 --> 51:20.293
What are you going to
Palm Beach for? A divorce.

51:21.935 --> 51:23.325
Well, you needn't look
so sour about it.

51:23.425 --> 51:25.660
Your sister's been divorced
five times, hasn't she?

51:25.760 --> 51:28.573
No, no, three,
she was annulled twice.

51:28.673 --> 51:30.908
Well, I've never been
divorced before. Good.

51:31.008 --> 51:32.731
By the way, what is your name?

51:32.831 --> 51:35.182
Oh, Jeffers.
Geraldine Jeffers.

51:35.567 --> 51:37.290
Was he brutal to you?

51:37.872 --> 51:40.107
Oh, not particularly.

51:40.207 --> 51:41.499
A drunkard, huh?

51:41.599 --> 51:44.316
No, not congenital,
or anything like that.

51:44.416 --> 51:46.620
Women always protect the
man they've been married to.

51:46.720 --> 51:48.633
Yes, I suppose
it's human nature.

51:48.733 --> 51:50.266
Did he beat you?

51:50.366 --> 51:51.879
Not often.

51:51.984 --> 51:53.244
The hound.

51:53.344 --> 51:56.891
Oh, a man's a man, I suppose. They're
all tarred with the same brush.

51:56.991 --> 52:00.254
How brave you are. When I
marry, there'll be no divorce.

52:00.354 --> 52:01.785
That's why I've been
a little cautious.

52:01.885 --> 52:03.801
You're afraid somebody
will marry you for your money.

52:03.901 --> 52:06.491
Oh, I expect that. When money
reaches certain proportions,

52:06.591 --> 52:08.415
you can't ignore it any more
than you can a...

52:08.515 --> 52:09.855
A horse in a bedroom.

52:09.955 --> 52:12.060
I wasn't thinking exactly
of that, but it'll serve.

52:12.160 --> 52:14.845
I see marriage as a
sort of permanent welding,

52:14.945 --> 52:16.318
a growing together
of two trees,

52:16.418 --> 52:18.751
in spite of anything my sister
can demonstrate to the contrary,

52:18.851 --> 52:20.860
into a sort of
permanent mess... Mass.

52:20.960 --> 52:25.005
Like a permanent grafting of
two trees into a permanent graft.

52:25.171 --> 52:27.099
Oh, that one's too easy.

52:27.199 --> 52:29.148
Oh, you mean
a permanent graft.

52:29.248 --> 52:30.332
I get it.

52:30.432 --> 52:32.607
But it doesn't have to be.
It can be very nice, I'm sure.

52:32.707 --> 52:34.081
Oh, it can be.

52:34.181 --> 52:36.928
And after the divorce,
you have plans? Oh, yes.

52:37.028 --> 52:39.231
Anybody I know? I know almost
everybody in Palm Beach.

52:39.331 --> 52:41.153
Oh, no,
I haven't picked him out yet.

52:41.253 --> 52:44.669
Just some very rich man.
Some very rich man?

52:44.769 --> 52:46.684
Oh, I wasn't thinking
of anyone as rich as you.

52:46.784 --> 52:47.933
That might get to be annoying.

52:48.033 --> 52:49.532
It is.
Is it?

52:49.632 --> 52:52.270
No, I just meant
somebody who's well-fixed.

52:53.012 --> 52:56.575
And who could spare the $99,000
without missing it too much.

52:56.675 --> 52:59.231
I'm not quite sure I
understand about the $99,000.

52:59.331 --> 53:02.593
Well, you see, he just
happens to need $99,000,

53:02.693 --> 53:04.832
and after all, I don't see any
reason why he shouldn't get it

53:04.932 --> 53:06.047
if I'm throwing it
out the windows.

53:06.147 --> 53:07.645
This is your last husband
you're talking about?

53:07.745 --> 53:09.855
Yes. He wants to sell you for $99,000.

53:09.955 --> 53:12.064
Oh, no, no. I don't think
he had any such idea at all.

53:12.164 --> 53:13.408
Well, what do you call it?

53:13.508 --> 53:16.477
Well, I mean, after all...
He's entitled to something.

53:16.577 --> 53:20.258
I mean, he did protect me and
give me food, such as it was,

53:20.358 --> 53:22.432
and clothes, such as they
were, for a few years and...

53:22.532 --> 53:25.439
And now if I can repay... But the
man is a vermin. No court of law...

53:25.539 --> 53:27.842
Don't you think I'm worth $99,000?
That has nothing to do with it.

53:27.942 --> 53:30.049
You're probably worth that,
twice that, three times,

53:30.149 --> 53:32.387
but even so, the days of
serfdom... I mean, bondage...

53:32.487 --> 53:34.496
I mean, the days you bought
a wife for a cow are over.

53:34.596 --> 53:36.257
I've never heard of
such a thing. I...

53:36.357 --> 53:38.797
Chivalry is not only dead,
it's decomposed.

53:39.158 --> 53:41.028
Well, how much
did this yacht cost you?

53:41.128 --> 53:43.298
That is entirely beside the
point. A woman is not a vessel.

53:43.398 --> 53:45.252
I mean, of all the filthy
things I've heard in my life,

53:45.352 --> 53:46.946
I still...
How does he want it?

53:47.046 --> 53:48.993
In cash, maybe?
In cash.

53:49.093 --> 53:51.073
So I won't stop the check,
the scoundrel...

53:51.173 --> 53:52.866
I don't mean me,
I mean that whoever's...

53:52.966 --> 53:56.449
Well, I don't think he'll ever
get it. It was just an idea.

53:56.549 --> 53:58.307
There is a name
for such reptiles,

53:58.407 --> 54:00.833
but I won't sully this sweet
ocean breeze by mentioning it.

54:00.933 --> 54:04.704
I may not be exactly in the best of
shape, but if ever I meet this Mr. Jeffers,

54:04.804 --> 54:06.369
I'll thrash him
within an inch of his life.

54:06.469 --> 54:08.481
Oh, well, then I hope
you never meet him.

54:08.581 --> 54:09.876
I suppose he's large?

54:09.976 --> 54:11.456
Well, he's not small.

54:11.556 --> 54:13.090
That's one of
the tragedies of this life.

54:13.190 --> 54:15.104
That the men who are
most in need of a beating-up,

54:15.204 --> 54:16.883
are always enormous.

54:24.184 --> 54:27.428
She's a tall, dark-haired girl with big
eyes. Yes, I know who you talking about.

54:27.528 --> 54:29.220
You mean the young lady
who lose all her clothes.

54:29.320 --> 54:30.369
Lost all her clothes?

54:30.469 --> 54:33.345
Yes, sir, but we fix her up with a
blanket when she got off at Jacksonville.

54:33.445 --> 54:34.660
She got off at Jacksonville?
Yes, sir.

54:34.760 --> 54:35.779
Alone?

54:35.879 --> 54:37.605
Well, you might
practically say she was alone.

54:37.705 --> 54:41.122
The gentleman that got off with her gave
me 10 cents from New York to Jacksonville.

54:41.222 --> 54:43.748
Watch your step, lady. She's
alone, but she don't know it.

54:43.848 --> 54:46.086
Well, never mind the philosophy.
Then she's at Jacksonville?

54:46.186 --> 54:47.178
Yes, sir. No, sir.

54:47.278 --> 54:50.147
She said that he said he was gonna
take her down there on his boat.

54:50.247 --> 54:51.941
I suppose she means yacht,

54:52.041 --> 54:54.375
but I don't see how no
gentleman can give me a dime

54:54.475 --> 54:56.808
from New York to Jacksonville
can have a yacht.

54:56.908 --> 55:00.688
Maybe a canoe or a bicycle.
Yes, sir.

55:20.540 --> 55:23.639
Hey, let me use these a
minute, will you? Surely.

55:43.100 --> 55:44.824
Thanks.
Any time.

55:48.957 --> 55:51.608
I think you'll like Palm Beach
very much.

55:53.374 --> 55:54.584
Yoo-hoo!

55:59.390 --> 56:00.839
Who's that?

56:00.939 --> 56:02.071
Oh, that's my sister,
the Princess.

56:02.302 --> 56:03.880
Hello, Maude.
Hello, Snoodles.

56:03.980 --> 56:06.186
Where'd you get the
pretty girl? Greetings.

56:06.286 --> 56:07.928
She calls me Snoodles.

56:08.447 --> 56:09.578
Is that the Prince?

56:09.678 --> 56:12.520
No, the Prince is all washed
up. This is something new.

56:12.620 --> 56:13.673
It might be a duke.

56:13.773 --> 56:16.011
It might be her tailor, too.
She goes out with anything.

56:16.111 --> 56:18.056
Hello, darling. What a
perfectly beautiful dame.

56:18.156 --> 56:20.330
Were you seasick on the way
down? Wherever did you find her?

56:20.430 --> 56:22.376
This is Toto. Say, "How do
you do," Toto. Greetings.

56:22.476 --> 56:25.724
Toto's a refugee from his
creditors, I think. Greetings.

56:29.599 --> 56:31.436
Glad to be aboard, sir.
Hello, Maude.

56:31.536 --> 56:33.162
Hello. Glad to see you aboard.
How do you do?

56:33.262 --> 56:34.987
You get prettier as one
gets nearer. Thank you.

56:35.087 --> 56:36.844
How did you manage it?
He's stiffer than a plank.

56:36.944 --> 56:38.252
This must have done him
a power of good.

56:38.352 --> 56:39.499
This is my sister
Maude, Mrs...

56:39.599 --> 56:41.098
Don't tell me he doesn't
even know your name.

56:41.198 --> 56:42.191
This is perfectly marvelous.

56:42.291 --> 56:43.661
Now, tell me
he picked you up on the train

56:43.761 --> 56:45.355
and you'll make me a
happy woman. Greetings.

56:45.455 --> 56:46.732
All right, Toto,
you've said, "How do you do."

56:46.832 --> 56:48.075
Wait till I tell the papers.

56:48.175 --> 56:49.673
You know, Maude, somebody
meeting you for the first time,

56:49.773 --> 56:51.850
not knowing you were cracked, might
get the wrong impression of you.

56:51.950 --> 56:53.228
Did he really pick you up
on the train?

56:53.328 --> 56:55.403
Well, I was in awful trouble
until he nobly came to my rescue.

56:55.503 --> 56:56.523
Oh, now you've spoiled
everything.

56:56.623 --> 56:58.219
I hoped for once
he hadn't done anything noble,

56:58.319 --> 56:59.532
that he was really cooking
with gas.

56:59.632 --> 57:01.389
What a lovely suit.
He bought me this.

57:01.489 --> 57:02.862
Why, Snoodles, you rat!

57:02.962 --> 57:05.420
We'll work this into something
yet. This is perfectly electrifying.

57:05.520 --> 57:07.402
You must come and stay with us
and we'll warm this up.

57:07.502 --> 57:08.588
You're divorced, of course.
No, not quite.

57:08.688 --> 57:11.439
That's marvelous. I don't think I'm
quite through with the Prince yet, either.

57:11.539 --> 57:12.515
We can look
for new husbands together.

57:12.615 --> 57:15.020
I'm thinking of an American at the
moment. It seems more patriotic.

57:15.120 --> 57:16.139
Greetings.
No, no, Toto.

57:16.239 --> 57:17.818
His English
is a little elementary.

57:20.515 --> 57:22.638
What language does he speak?
I don't know.

57:22.738 --> 57:25.099
I think it's Baluchistan,
but it's impossible to tell.

57:25.199 --> 57:26.636
Hello.
Let's go ashore now.

57:26.736 --> 57:29.073
I'll put you in the blue suite
and we'll have a wonderful time.

57:29.173 --> 57:30.734
You're perfectly respectable,
but of course,

57:30.834 --> 57:33.325
as long as we don't roll on the
floor and give the butler hysterics,

57:33.425 --> 57:35.631
we'll be cooking on the front
burner. I talk a lot, don't I?

57:35.731 --> 57:38.781
Yes. Snoodles, you snake in the grass...

57:41.538 --> 57:43.435
Did you have to get him drunk
or how did you do it?

57:43.535 --> 57:45.420
You'll have to tell me
all about it later. Maude.

57:45.520 --> 57:47.469
Look at that very handsome
man. I wonder who he is.

57:47.569 --> 57:49.004
I don't think
I've seen him around before.

57:49.104 --> 57:51.020
I thought I knew all the
handsome men in this village.

57:51.120 --> 57:52.270
We could use some new faces.

57:52.370 --> 57:54.413
Oh, it isn't possible.
What isn't possible?

57:54.513 --> 57:58.242
I think I know that man.
In fact, I'm sure of it.

58:03.875 --> 58:05.454
What did you follow me
down here for, anyway?

58:05.554 --> 58:07.312
What do you mean, what did
I follow you down here for?

58:07.412 --> 58:09.326
You're my wife, aren't you?
You're making an ass of yourself

58:09.426 --> 58:10.673
exposing yourself
to all sorts of dangers

58:10.773 --> 58:12.368
that I promised to love,
honor, and protect you from.

58:12.468 --> 58:14.479
But that isn't fair when you
realize I'm doing this for you, too.

58:14.579 --> 58:15.728
I don't want you
to do any more.

58:15.828 --> 58:17.651
But, look, I've left you.
I'm not your wife any longer.

58:17.751 --> 58:19.183
You're not my husband.
Gerry, darling...

58:19.283 --> 58:22.020
No, no, stop... Well, I
must say you do know him.

58:22.438 --> 58:26.831
This is the Princess Centimillia.
My brother, Captain McGlue.

58:26.931 --> 58:28.593
What? Captain, we should have met sooner

58:28.693 --> 58:30.257
and if I'd seen you around,
we would have.

58:30.357 --> 58:32.401
This is my brother Captain
Hackensacker, Captain McGlue.

58:32.501 --> 58:33.747
That's an odd name.
Yes, isn't it?

58:33.847 --> 58:35.279
How do you do, Captain.
I'm not a captain.

58:35.379 --> 58:36.978
That's my sister's joke
because I own a yacht.

58:37.078 --> 58:39.056
That's my sister's joke
because I don't own one.

58:39.156 --> 58:40.149
Very glad to meet you.

58:40.249 --> 58:41.777
Your sister didn't tell me
she had a brother here.

58:41.877 --> 58:43.824
No, I just dropped over...
You're staying with us, of course.

58:43.924 --> 58:45.268
No, we wouldn't want
to inconvenience you.

58:45.368 --> 58:46.546
We'll go to a hotel.
No, but, Mac...

58:46.646 --> 58:49.039
Inconvenience us? Bumble puppy.
We practically run a hotel, anyway.

58:49.139 --> 58:51.892
This will give the servants some
exercise. I won't take no for an answer.

58:51.992 --> 58:53.235
Your brother's
a very fine looking man.

58:53.335 --> 58:54.897
You know
you look exactly alike.

58:54.997 --> 58:56.113
I suppose he's married.

58:56.213 --> 58:57.680
No, no, he's entirely free.

58:57.780 --> 58:58.802
You don't tell me.
Now, look.

58:58.902 --> 58:59.895
Don't pay any attention
to her, Captain,

58:59.995 --> 59:02.163
her bark is worse than her
bite. That's what you think.

59:02.263 --> 59:04.176
Oh, dear, I wish I hadn't
brought Toto along today.

59:04.276 --> 59:07.093
Somebody think of an errand
to send him on.

59:07.193 --> 59:09.331
Hello.
Toto, this is Captain McGlue.

59:09.431 --> 59:11.857
I'm going to see more of him
and less of you from now on.

59:11.957 --> 59:13.813
Hello.
Listen carefully, dear.

59:13.913 --> 59:17.491
I left my handkerchief on the
yacht. You go fetch it, see?

59:17.591 --> 59:18.992
Nitz.
Yitz, Toto.

59:19.092 --> 59:21.732
Nitz.
It'll be nitz to you, Toto.

59:23.977 --> 59:26.695
And now, Captain,
you may take my arm.

59:27.049 --> 59:29.458
What did you say
you were captain of?

59:29.558 --> 59:30.806
I didn't say a word about it.

59:30.906 --> 59:33.395
How wonderful it is meeting
a silent American again.

59:33.495 --> 59:36.339
All my husbands were
foreigners and such chatterboxes

59:36.439 --> 59:38.549
I could hardly get
a word in edgeways.

59:38.649 --> 59:40.918
They make a handsome
couple, don't they? Pardon?

59:41.018 --> 59:43.669
My sister and your brother. It would
be nice if something came of it.

59:43.769 --> 59:46.643
Oh, yes, wouldn't it?

59:46.743 --> 59:48.406
It would be wonderful for him.

59:48.506 --> 59:50.646
Of course, she's no bargain,
but it might happen very easily.

59:50.746 --> 59:52.244
She's a woman
of iron determination

59:52.344 --> 59:54.772
and once her mind is made up,
he might as well yield.

59:54.872 --> 59:56.086
I can see what you mean.

59:56.186 --> 59:58.261
I'm glad you're going to stay
with us and your brother, too.

59:58.361 --> 01:00:00.216
Are you? I don't know
why I didn't think of it

01:00:00.316 --> 01:00:01.307
or maybe I did think of it,

01:00:01.407 --> 01:00:03.671
but it took someone of my sister's
courage to make it come true.

01:00:03.771 --> 01:00:05.813
You're very sweet.
Thank you very much.

01:00:05.913 --> 01:00:08.308
The Captain's a big fellow,
isn't he? Yes, isn't he?

01:00:08.408 --> 01:00:10.934
You look exactly alike.
Yes, don't we?

01:00:11.034 --> 01:00:13.573
You know,
people always remark on it.

01:00:23.083 --> 01:00:24.855
Why don't you marry her?
She's lovely.

01:00:24.955 --> 01:00:26.232
In the first place,
she isn't free yet.

01:00:26.332 --> 01:00:29.048
In the second place, you don't marry
somebody you just met the day before.

01:00:29.148 --> 01:00:30.872
At least I don't.
But that's the only way, dear.

01:00:30.972 --> 01:00:33.144
If you get to know too much about
them, you'd never marry them.

01:00:33.244 --> 01:00:35.385
I'd marry Captain McGlue
tomorrow even with that name.

01:00:35.485 --> 01:00:36.477
And divorce him next month.

01:00:36.577 --> 01:00:39.031
Nothing is permanent in this
world except Roosevelt, dear.

01:00:39.131 --> 01:00:42.006
As a matter of fact, Maude, I'm becoming
very attracted to this young woman,

01:00:42.106 --> 01:00:44.535
more so than anyone I've known
the same length of time.

01:00:44.635 --> 01:00:47.063
But I want to know how she is
early in the morning, late at night,

01:00:47.163 --> 01:00:50.745
rain or shine, under trying circumstances
as when the servants leave in a body.

01:00:50.845 --> 01:00:53.238
How she is with children... What
are you going to do, rent some?

01:00:53.338 --> 01:00:54.456
Why not?
Perhaps we could borrow some.

01:00:54.556 --> 01:00:55.704
You mean a mock marriage?

01:00:55.804 --> 01:00:59.483
I certainly do not. I revere marriage
unlike some people I could mention.

01:00:59.583 --> 01:01:00.664
Oh, here.

01:01:00.764 --> 01:01:04.152
But why "Captain McGlue"
of all the idiotic names?

01:01:04.252 --> 01:01:07.289
Because I want him to build
your airport for you, darling.

01:01:07.389 --> 01:01:09.147
Now he seems to have
something against my husband.

01:01:09.247 --> 01:01:11.224
I don't know why, but
as my brother... Yes.

01:01:11.324 --> 01:01:14.232
Apart from the fact that I wouldn't
even let him build a chicken coop for me,

01:01:14.332 --> 01:01:16.409
I'd still like to know why I'm
to be called Captain McGlue.

01:01:16.509 --> 01:01:18.488
Of all the nincompoopish...
Wasn't that your mother's name?

01:01:18.588 --> 01:01:20.984
What? Captain McGlue?
Really, Geraldine.

01:01:21.084 --> 01:01:23.448
Her name was McGrew.
M-C-G-R-E-W.

01:01:23.548 --> 01:01:26.300
Oh, well, I'm sorry, darling.
I remembered it as McGlue.

01:01:26.400 --> 01:01:28.475
Yes. Well, I guess I'm stuck
with it now.

01:01:28.575 --> 01:01:31.416
Captain McGlue. What am I supposed
to be captain of? A garbage scow?

01:01:31.516 --> 01:01:33.243
No, I just put that in
to make it more dignified.

01:01:33.343 --> 01:01:34.970
Couldn't you have been
a captain in the last war?

01:01:35.070 --> 01:01:38.438
Sure, I was 11 years old at the
finish. A captain in knee britches.

01:01:38.671 --> 01:01:40.665
What about the Boy Scouts?
Wonderful.

01:01:40.765 --> 01:01:43.419
I could go around building bonfires
on the drawing room carpets.

01:01:43.519 --> 01:01:45.628
I'm sorry, darling. I
really meant it for the best.

01:01:45.729 --> 01:01:48.316
I know you did. That's
what's so irritating about it.

01:01:48.416 --> 01:01:49.851
Where'd you get
the brother idea?

01:01:49.951 --> 01:01:51.262
Because you had your arms
around me.

01:01:51.362 --> 01:01:53.819
I suppose no one's ever had his
arms around you except your brother,

01:01:53.919 --> 01:01:54.896
only, you haven't got one.

01:01:54.996 --> 01:01:57.883
I don't suppose Captain Hackensacker
ever put his arms around you.

01:01:57.983 --> 01:01:59.359
Of course not.
Of course not.

01:01:59.459 --> 01:02:01.980
Yachts must have changed since
the last time I was on one.

01:02:02.080 --> 01:02:03.871
That's what
they build yachts for.

01:02:03.971 --> 01:02:07.419
Naturally, he will put his arms
around me when and if we're engaged.

01:02:07.519 --> 01:02:09.085
Oh, we're engaged now, are we?

01:02:09.185 --> 01:02:10.560
Is there anything wrong
with being engaged?

01:02:10.660 --> 01:02:11.773
You ought to know.

01:02:11.873 --> 01:02:13.216
Where'd you get that suit?

01:02:13.316 --> 01:02:15.324
That's what
I was telling you about.

01:02:15.424 --> 01:02:16.670
What's that
you've got on your wrist?

01:02:16.770 --> 01:02:18.624
Just what you think
it is, dear.

01:02:18.724 --> 01:02:20.220
What kind of stones are those?

01:02:20.320 --> 01:02:21.917
Exactly what they look like.

01:02:22.017 --> 01:02:24.638
You know what it feels like to
be strangled with bare hands?

01:02:24.738 --> 01:02:26.910
Oh, now,
wait a minute, darling.

01:02:27.010 --> 01:02:30.639
I've always been on the level
with you and I always will be.

01:02:32.404 --> 01:02:34.591
Here.
What's that supposed to be?

01:02:34.691 --> 01:02:37.163
You put that over
on the mantelpiece.

01:02:39.380 --> 01:02:40.841
Lovebirds, huh?

01:02:41.139 --> 01:02:42.815
Now, so long as that's there,

01:02:42.915 --> 01:02:46.079
you won't have the slightest,
smallest thing to be unhappy about.

01:02:46.179 --> 01:02:49.085
That'll be a signal and we'll
never have to mention the subject.

01:02:49.185 --> 01:02:51.165
And that goes for you, too.
Huh?

01:02:51.265 --> 01:02:54.237
And your friend the Princess, you
seem to be cutting such a groove with.

01:02:54.337 --> 01:02:55.389
Princess.

01:02:55.489 --> 01:02:57.762
Say, where'd you get the money
to fly down here, anyway?

01:02:57.862 --> 01:03:01.058
Same place you got yours, only,
I didn't have to kiss him goodbye.

01:03:01.158 --> 01:03:03.051
Oh, the Wienie King.

01:03:03.669 --> 01:03:07.777
He wanted us to get back together, I
guess. Don't you think we owe it to him?

01:03:07.877 --> 01:03:11.009
Look, why don't you let me go out there
and poke that guy in the nose just once?

01:03:11.109 --> 01:03:13.346
Because I've left you,
darling, for both our good.

01:03:13.446 --> 01:03:14.438
Now, just...
Excuse me.

01:03:14.538 --> 01:03:16.770
Mac, did you happen to... You don't
mind if I call you Mac, do you?

01:03:16.870 --> 01:03:18.178
Did you happen to bring
a tuxedo with you?

01:03:18.278 --> 01:03:20.418
I did not. The business I came
here to tend to didn't call for one

01:03:20.518 --> 01:03:22.819
and you can stop pulling my
coat. That's perfectly all right.

01:03:22.919 --> 01:03:25.603
In a pinch you can wear one of mine.
Oh, in a pinch. That's very funny.

01:03:25.703 --> 01:03:27.075
I won't be here that long.
Why, Mac.

01:03:27.175 --> 01:03:29.184
That's too bad, old man. I hoped
you'd spend the season with us.

01:03:29.284 --> 01:03:30.305
I wanted
to get to know you better.

01:03:30.405 --> 01:03:32.740
In any case, there's something I
wanna talk to you about before you go.

01:03:32.840 --> 01:03:34.239
I'm very glad you showed up
just when you did.

01:03:34.339 --> 01:03:35.360
So am I.
Good.

01:03:35.460 --> 01:03:36.927
I needed a male member
of Gerry's family.

01:03:37.027 --> 01:03:38.048
You have him.
Fine.

01:03:38.148 --> 01:03:39.200
Now, I have
a certain thought...

01:03:39.300 --> 01:03:41.183
I have a certain thought also,
and it's that bracelet.

01:03:41.283 --> 01:03:42.946
Mac... I'm very glad
you brought that up.

01:03:43.046 --> 01:03:45.284
Mac is delighted with it,
Snoodles. He shouldn't be.

01:03:45.384 --> 01:03:46.465
He isn't.
Fine.

01:03:46.565 --> 01:03:49.058
The first bracelet my sister got, I
punched the fellow right in the nose.

01:03:49.158 --> 01:03:50.135
Fellow by the name of Wallace.

01:03:50.235 --> 01:03:51.842
I can see we understand
each other perfectly.

01:03:51.942 --> 01:03:54.466
I didn't like it any more than you
do this. You're reading my mind.

01:03:54.566 --> 01:03:56.609
Splendid. But there's a difference
between Wallace and me...

01:03:56.709 --> 01:03:58.112
I'm not interested in Wallace.

01:03:58.212 --> 01:03:59.297
There's no reason
why you should be.

01:03:59.397 --> 01:04:00.675
Now, I, on the other hand...
Now, look.

01:04:00.775 --> 01:04:03.201
If I could trust you two boys
not to slug each other,

01:04:03.301 --> 01:04:05.378
I'd like to make
an exit right about here.

01:04:05.478 --> 01:04:07.361
I feel like a bone
between two dogs.

01:04:07.461 --> 01:04:09.092
Oh, we're going to
get along together, all right.

01:04:09.192 --> 01:04:10.691
There's nothing the matter
with my intentions,

01:04:10.791 --> 01:04:12.226
as Mac will be
the first to admit.

01:04:12.326 --> 01:04:13.859
The only thing that could
possibly embarrass you

01:04:13.959 --> 01:04:17.703
would be the lovely things I want to say
to him about you. Your face, your form.

01:04:17.803 --> 01:04:20.134
Things that a brother is
naturally blind to. Is that so?

01:04:20.234 --> 01:04:22.211
Geraldine's future
and this little plan I have,

01:04:22.311 --> 01:04:23.557
which I'd better discuss
with you before...

01:04:23.657 --> 01:04:25.667
What's buzzing, cousins? What's
the dirt? Never mind now, Maude.

01:04:25.767 --> 01:04:27.429
It's just a little something
I want to discuss with Mac.

01:04:27.529 --> 01:04:30.052
My dear, when you hear what
it is, you will simply expire.

01:04:30.152 --> 01:04:31.129
Maude...

01:04:31.229 --> 01:04:33.350
It's too, too excruciating!
Maude, please.

01:04:33.450 --> 01:04:35.304
He wants a miniature
marriage with you.

01:04:35.404 --> 01:04:37.736
A miniature what? Go away,
Toto. This is not for children.

01:04:37.836 --> 01:04:40.260
You know, everything up to the dissolve
and then good night, sweetheart,

01:04:40.360 --> 01:04:41.925
I'll see you in the morning.
What's this?

01:04:42.025 --> 01:04:44.498
The boy wants to bundle.
Maude!

01:04:45.146 --> 01:04:47.847
And then he's going to make you
cook and sew and wash the windows,

01:04:47.947 --> 01:04:49.509
and then he's going
to get some little brats

01:04:49.609 --> 01:04:51.205
to see if you know how
to change them.

01:04:51.305 --> 01:04:53.543
But how?
He's going to rent them.

01:04:53.643 --> 01:04:54.903
Oh, no.

01:04:55.290 --> 01:04:57.765
Come on, let's you and me go
someplace. They want to be alone.

01:04:57.865 --> 01:04:59.975
But just a minute, I... Oh,
don't take it so seriously.

01:05:00.075 --> 01:05:01.320
They want to bake a cake,
dear.

01:05:01.420 --> 01:05:03.159
They want to bake a...

01:05:05.468 --> 01:05:08.103
I don't know what to say. I
didn't realize it was so humorous.

01:05:08.203 --> 01:05:10.823
Did you really want
to put me through all that?

01:05:10.923 --> 01:05:13.030
I'm afraid I'm... There's no
use trying to conceal it now.

01:05:13.130 --> 01:05:14.311
I might have guessed it
on the train.

01:05:14.411 --> 01:05:16.583
I certainly should have known it
in Jacksonville and on the yacht.

01:05:16.683 --> 01:05:20.296
The trial was as much for you as for me
and however ridiculous I may seem in this,

01:05:20.397 --> 01:05:22.855
nothing ridiculous about
the way I feel in my heart.

01:05:22.955 --> 01:05:24.665
I'm madly in love with you.

01:05:25.853 --> 01:05:27.496
Oh, isn't that pretty?

01:05:27.596 --> 01:05:28.905
Why do you keep bothering
them all the time?

01:05:29.005 --> 01:05:31.378
If you want to
bother somebody, bother me.

01:05:33.405 --> 01:05:35.178
You know, I'm not sure
that Mac likes me.

01:05:35.278 --> 01:05:36.936
Oh, no, no, no,
he's always like that.

01:05:37.036 --> 01:05:40.201
It's just that he doesn't seem to
think anybody's good enough for me.

01:05:40.301 --> 01:05:41.846
Well, he's right there.

01:05:54.431 --> 01:05:56.170
You don't care much for me,
do you?

01:05:56.270 --> 01:05:57.684
Why, certainly.

01:05:57.790 --> 01:05:59.751
Then why do you let me
flop around?

01:05:59.851 --> 01:06:01.595
I'm sorry.

01:06:02.431 --> 01:06:04.327
You will care for me, though.

01:06:04.427 --> 01:06:07.480
I grow on people, like moss.

01:06:09.023 --> 01:06:11.390
Sit down, Toto.
Stop following me around.

01:06:12.736 --> 01:06:15.037
Nitz.
Yitz, Toto.

01:06:29.824 --> 01:06:32.028
Isn't it romantic?

01:06:34.977 --> 01:06:36.847
Oh, you have
a nice little voice.

01:06:36.947 --> 01:06:38.443
Thank you.
I used to sing in college.

01:06:38.543 --> 01:06:41.261
With a mandolin? I wouldn't
play it around the house.

01:06:41.361 --> 01:06:42.670
Would you be around
the house much?

01:06:42.770 --> 01:06:45.965
Not any more than you wanted me. I have
an office, not that I do much in it.

01:06:46.065 --> 01:06:48.236
Say, perhaps Mac
could come and help me.

01:06:48.336 --> 01:06:49.964
Oh, that would be wonderful.

01:06:50.064 --> 01:06:53.197
You two could plan the airport
together. What airport is that?

01:06:53.297 --> 01:06:55.242
The most remarkable invention
you've ever heard of,

01:06:55.342 --> 01:06:57.582
a suspended airport right
in the middle of the city,

01:06:57.682 --> 01:06:58.926
stretched like
a tennis racket.

01:06:59.026 --> 01:07:01.613
But would it be strong enough? I
mean, after all, a tennis racket.

01:07:01.713 --> 01:07:03.568
What's Gerry's husband like?
Who?

01:07:03.668 --> 01:07:05.611
Oh, just a flop.
A big flop?

01:07:05.711 --> 01:07:07.673
Yes, any way you'd take it.

01:07:07.811 --> 01:07:10.829
Well, he won't be such a flop
with his $99,000.

01:07:10.929 --> 01:07:13.696
Snoodles will give it to him,
all right. And why not?

01:07:13.858 --> 01:07:16.706
I ought to marry him and
get it back into the family.

01:07:16.866 --> 01:07:21.040
That would be a big joke. Of
course, I'm crazy, I'll marry anyone.

01:07:21.140 --> 01:07:23.020
What's this about $99,000?

01:07:23.120 --> 01:07:24.173
I might be able to help him.

01:07:24.273 --> 01:07:26.479
In fact, I will be able to help
him. In fact, I'll help him. Why not?

01:07:26.579 --> 01:07:29.037
Will you really? Of course I
will, up to a certain point.

01:07:29.137 --> 01:07:30.480
How much
would a working model cost?

01:07:30.580 --> 01:07:33.517
$99... I mean, $100,000,
in that neighborhood.

01:07:33.617 --> 01:07:35.694
That shouldn't be a very
difficult neighborhood to find.

01:07:35.794 --> 01:07:37.196
I think I'll be able
to do it, all right.

01:07:37.296 --> 01:07:39.310
Oh, really?
You've made me so happy.

01:07:39.410 --> 01:07:41.201
You don't know
how much trouble he's had.

01:07:41.301 --> 01:07:42.293
Is that so?

01:07:42.393 --> 01:07:44.723
He won't know what trouble really
is till he tangles up with Maude.

01:07:44.823 --> 01:07:46.675
Oh, that's rather unkind.
I shouldn't have said it.

01:07:46.775 --> 01:07:49.165
You say about $100,000?
Exactly $100,000.

01:07:49.265 --> 01:07:50.497
It's built.

01:07:52.261 --> 01:07:55.791
You mean her husband wants $99,000
before he'll give her a divorce?

01:07:55.891 --> 01:07:59.343
Oh, I love you like this, with
lightning flashing out of your eyes.

01:07:59.443 --> 01:08:00.819
Did she tell you that story?

01:08:00.919 --> 01:08:03.024
Why should we talk about
that heel when you're here?

01:08:03.124 --> 01:08:04.207
Did she tell you that?

01:08:04.307 --> 01:08:06.735
Do that again. I love it.
Listen...

01:08:06.835 --> 01:08:09.107
Oh, Snoodles,
that's wonderful!

01:08:09.207 --> 01:08:11.059
Tom... Mac will be wild
with excitement.

01:08:11.159 --> 01:08:13.875
You know, when you've waited
so long. Not at all, not at all.

01:08:13.975 --> 01:08:15.407
I'm delighted
to have the opportunity.

01:08:15.507 --> 01:08:18.064
Look... Darling, I have
the most wonderful news.

01:08:18.165 --> 01:08:20.176
Snoodles is going to build
your airport for you.

01:08:20.276 --> 01:08:21.679
Why should he build it?
I'll build it.

01:08:21.779 --> 01:08:23.392
You don't even know
what it is, Maude.

01:08:24.615 --> 01:08:25.712
Quiet, Toto.

01:08:25.813 --> 01:08:27.727
Well, that gives us a lot to
look forward to, doesn't it?

01:08:27.827 --> 01:08:28.977
I don't know
if I've told you, Mac,

01:08:29.077 --> 01:08:31.763
but your sister and I have progressed
considerably since this afternoon.

01:08:31.863 --> 01:08:33.010
Oh, is that so?

01:08:33.109 --> 01:08:34.835
What's all this business
about your husband

01:08:34.935 --> 01:08:37.652
wanting $99,000
before he sets you free?

01:08:37.752 --> 01:08:39.573
Oh, that was just an idea
that he had.

01:08:39.673 --> 01:08:41.493
You know how people are
when they're upset.

01:08:41.593 --> 01:08:43.471
I'm not sure
that he actually meant it.

01:08:43.572 --> 01:08:46.194
Let's not even talk about it.
No, no, let's face it.

01:08:46.295 --> 01:08:48.532
Gerry naturally wants to
defend this human bacterium.

01:08:48.631 --> 01:08:50.356
Of course, that's only natural
and gallant.

01:08:50.456 --> 01:08:52.245
But the fact of the matter is,
he's asked her for it,

01:08:52.345 --> 01:08:53.970
and as soon as my name
comes into it, we're doomed.

01:08:54.071 --> 01:08:55.412
Broiled.
As a Hackensacker,

01:08:55.513 --> 01:08:57.426
I find it cheaper to pay
than to fight.

01:08:57.526 --> 01:09:00.790
Of course, $99,000 isn't a small sum,
but on the other hand, it isn't large.

01:09:00.890 --> 01:09:02.964
I should say not.
Why, when I think of Stefan,

01:09:03.064 --> 01:09:05.426
to say nothing of Serge,
or that big one with the scar,

01:09:05.526 --> 01:09:07.488
what was his name?
Itsk.

01:09:07.721 --> 01:09:09.332
Baron Itsk, Lucius.

01:09:09.432 --> 01:09:11.075
Itsk?
Nitzk, Toto.

01:09:11.273 --> 01:09:13.429
I'm awfully sorry
to hear that about Tom.

01:09:13.529 --> 01:09:17.653
I knew he was a failure and a dreamer, I
guess, but I didn't know he was a skunk.

01:09:17.752 --> 01:09:20.595
It's very kind of you to want to build
the airport. I mean, the model of it.

01:09:20.694 --> 01:09:22.453
I guess I was a little
too stunned to say thank you,

01:09:22.554 --> 01:09:25.816
but you know how it is when you've been
waiting for something for a long time.

01:09:25.916 --> 01:09:27.638
There's only one trouble
with the whole setup,

01:09:27.738 --> 01:09:30.006
something that Gerry neglected
to tell you.

01:09:30.107 --> 01:09:32.051
That is that I'm not alone
in this invention.

01:09:32.151 --> 01:09:34.676
That human bacterium we were
talking about, her husband,

01:09:34.776 --> 01:09:36.787
has had exactly as much
to do with it as I have.

01:09:36.888 --> 01:09:39.251
So, you see, if you help me,
you'd be helping him, too.

01:09:39.350 --> 01:09:41.746
I know that nothing could
be further from your wish.

01:09:41.845 --> 01:09:43.939
How about dancing
with your brother?

01:09:46.571 --> 01:09:48.872
Shut up, Toto.
My brother is thinking.

01:09:49.067 --> 01:09:51.443
What did you have
to do that for, you fat-head?

01:09:51.542 --> 01:09:53.816
Don't you ever get tired
of being noble?

01:09:53.916 --> 01:09:56.341
Everything I build up for you,
you knock down.

01:09:56.441 --> 01:09:58.615
I've got you the money twice
already. Look, darling...

01:09:58.715 --> 01:10:01.433
No, no, I don't want to listen to
anything that begins with, "Look, darling,"

01:10:01.533 --> 01:10:03.925
so that you can get off
another noble saying.

01:10:04.025 --> 01:10:05.817
Can't you ever learn
to be practical?

01:10:05.917 --> 01:10:08.601
Don't you know that the greatest
men in the world have told lies

01:10:08.701 --> 01:10:11.514
and let things be misunderstood
if it was useful to them?

01:10:11.614 --> 01:10:13.720
Didn't you ever hear
of a campaign promise?

01:10:13.820 --> 01:10:16.057
The way you are is the
way you have to be, honey.

01:10:16.157 --> 01:10:18.426
That's the way I am. If
I'm supposed to be a flop...

01:10:18.526 --> 01:10:20.282
You're not going to be a flop.

01:10:20.382 --> 01:10:23.578
Nobody who's been married to me for
five years is going to be a flop.

01:10:23.678 --> 01:10:27.306
You're going to get your airport if
I have to build it for you myself.

01:10:27.469 --> 01:10:30.535
After I'm married.
After you're married.

01:10:31.533 --> 01:10:33.956
That's a funny thing
to hear your wife say.

01:10:36.430 --> 01:10:38.105
I've got it. I'll build it.

01:10:38.205 --> 01:10:40.955
His share will be more than $99,000,
so he'll have to release you.

01:10:41.055 --> 01:10:42.681
Whose share? That
scoundrel she's married to.

01:10:42.781 --> 01:10:44.759
Isn't that brilliant? It's the
first bright thought he's ever had.

01:10:44.859 --> 01:10:46.650
That's marvelous.
It was really very simple.

01:10:46.750 --> 01:10:47.929
Now, shall we change partners?

01:10:48.029 --> 01:10:49.560
It seems a shame to waste
such a beautiful sister

01:10:49.660 --> 01:10:52.744
upon a brother that doesn't
appreciate her. You said it.

01:11:08.591 --> 01:11:11.292
Thank you so much.
It was delightful.

01:11:11.392 --> 01:11:12.783
Not at all.

01:11:14.864 --> 01:11:16.572
Oh, dear.
What's the matter?

01:11:16.672 --> 01:11:19.129
We must have forgotten
Toto someplace. Is that so?

01:11:19.229 --> 01:11:21.788
I suppose he'll show up,
though. He always does.

01:11:21.888 --> 01:11:23.696
Greetings.
Ah, yes.

01:11:24.945 --> 01:11:28.174
Wouldn't he be awful to be
married to? Always hanging around.

01:11:36.401 --> 01:11:39.322
Captain, you have renewed
my faith in mankind.

01:11:39.422 --> 01:11:41.930
Well, there's nothing
like saving your faith.

01:11:42.257 --> 01:11:45.724
You are too, too divine.
You're a very embarrassing lady.

01:11:45.824 --> 01:11:47.582
If I weren't a little bit
mixed up at the moment,

01:11:47.682 --> 01:11:50.523
I'd take you up on a few of your
dares and make you say "papa."

01:11:50.623 --> 01:11:51.755
"Papa?"

01:11:52.626 --> 01:11:54.334
How would you like to go
to Fort Myers tomorrow?

01:11:54.434 --> 01:11:56.573
There's nothing there,
but the ride might be nice.

01:11:56.673 --> 01:11:58.301
We might put Toto in the Army.

01:11:58.401 --> 01:11:59.394
I may not be here tomorrow.

01:11:59.494 --> 01:12:00.890
What do you mean,
you may not be here tomorrow?

01:12:00.990 --> 01:12:03.420
I'm a little bit mixed up, but I sort
of have an appointment in New York.

01:12:03.520 --> 01:12:06.109
Oh, let her wait, whoever she
is. She's no good for you anyway.

01:12:06.209 --> 01:12:07.454
While I on the other hand...

01:12:07.554 --> 01:12:09.597
You never think of anything,
but topic "A," do you?

01:12:09.697 --> 01:12:11.243
Is there anything else?

01:12:11.379 --> 01:12:14.641
I'll leave you with that thought,
Captain. Bonsoir, drip-drap.

01:12:48.981 --> 01:12:50.542
Oh, dear.

01:12:50.773 --> 01:12:52.162
You're very kind.

01:12:52.262 --> 01:12:54.206
I think this is
the happiest night of my life.

01:12:54.306 --> 01:12:56.254
Oh, really, Snoodles?
Yes.

01:12:56.354 --> 01:12:59.199
You've freed me of a certain timidity,
from which I've always suffered.

01:12:59.299 --> 01:13:01.889
And now, with you and Mac
and the airport,

01:13:01.989 --> 01:13:04.577
I can see great days ahead,
full of fun and everything.

01:13:04.677 --> 01:13:06.051
Oh, I'm sure of it, Snoodles.

01:13:06.151 --> 01:13:08.095
By the way, I have a little
surprise for you in a few minutes,

01:13:08.195 --> 01:13:09.216
so don't be surprised.

01:13:09.316 --> 01:13:10.627
What is it?
If I told you what it is

01:13:10.727 --> 01:13:12.515
then it wouldn't be
a surprise anymore.

01:13:12.615 --> 01:13:16.032
Well, I wouldn't do anything too
surprising if I were you, Snoodles.

01:13:16.132 --> 01:13:18.370
You never can tell how those
things are going to turn out.

01:13:18.470 --> 01:13:21.758
I'm persuaded you'll be delighted.
Well, I certainly hope I will be.

01:13:21.858 --> 01:13:23.425
If you'll just leave your
window open onto the balcony.

01:13:23.525 --> 01:13:24.495
What?

01:13:24.595 --> 01:13:25.535
What was that?

01:13:25.635 --> 01:13:27.519
Oh, I didn't hear anything.
Good night, Snoodles.

01:13:27.619 --> 01:13:29.023
I'll see you in a little
while, then. Good night.

01:13:29.123 --> 01:13:32.308
I'll see you in my dreams.
Yes, that's a very good place.

01:13:40.856 --> 01:13:42.369
You're a fast worker,
aren't you?

01:13:42.469 --> 01:13:43.781
You have your nerve to talk.

01:13:43.881 --> 01:13:46.721
So you couldn't even wait a decent
interval, you and your princess.

01:13:46.821 --> 01:13:49.711
I hope you're very proud
of yourself, Captain McGlue.

01:13:51.161 --> 01:13:54.244
Wait a minute! No, let
me go, you big pullover.

01:13:54.344 --> 01:13:56.979
No, no, I just broke that
because it was handy.

01:13:57.081 --> 01:13:59.846
Oh, well, then you ought to be
ashamed of yourself.

01:13:59.946 --> 01:14:01.377
I'm the one
who has the right to...

01:14:01.477 --> 01:14:02.914
I know I'm an idiot,
but I suppose it's...

01:14:03.014 --> 01:14:05.092
When you've been fond of
somebody for a long time you...

01:14:05.192 --> 01:14:06.690
You shouldn't
have come down here.

01:14:06.790 --> 01:14:08.069
You had no right
to come down here.

01:14:08.169 --> 01:14:10.821
You should have given me a little
time to get used to the idea.

01:14:10.921 --> 01:14:12.322
Maybe I should,

01:14:12.422 --> 01:14:14.468
but you can't blame a man for
trying to hold on to something

01:14:14.568 --> 01:14:18.034
that he loves, that he always
has loved, and always will love.

01:14:18.298 --> 01:14:20.356
You're going to make me cry.
Gerry...

01:14:20.456 --> 01:14:24.005
No, you're forgetting the airport.
You're forgetting everything that counts.

01:14:24.105 --> 01:14:26.391
Gerry...
No! It's all finished.

01:14:26.842 --> 01:14:29.251
When you make a decision,
you have to stand by it,

01:14:29.351 --> 01:14:32.838
and you can't let champagne,
or tree toads,

01:14:32.938 --> 01:14:35.624
or night flowers, or
memories get in the way of it.

01:14:35.724 --> 01:14:38.024
It's all over,
and I know it's for the best.

01:14:38.124 --> 01:14:39.302
But, Gerry, I...

01:14:39.402 --> 01:14:41.764
Oh, no, now, listen to me
just this once, will you?

01:14:41.864 --> 01:14:45.254
I've always done what you wanted,
and it's always turned out a disaster.

01:14:45.354 --> 01:14:47.828
Good night, darling.
Sleep tight.

01:14:49.532 --> 01:14:51.881
It'll be funny sleeping with
a sitting room between us.

01:14:51.981 --> 01:14:55.128
And the doors locked. You
don't have to worry about that.

01:14:56.092 --> 01:14:58.231
Nevertheless.
Good night, dear.

01:14:59.549 --> 01:15:00.543
What?

01:15:00.643 --> 01:15:02.150
Well, don't you kiss
your brother good night?

01:15:02.250 --> 01:15:04.106
I don't know,
I never had a brother.

01:15:04.206 --> 01:15:05.465
You have one now.

01:15:06.845 --> 01:15:08.371
You fool.

01:15:13.629 --> 01:15:14.971
What's that?

01:15:25.918 --> 01:15:28.504
Good night,
sweetheart

01:15:28.670 --> 01:15:32.379
Till we meet tomorrow

01:15:32.861 --> 01:15:35.796
Good night, sweetheart

01:15:36.158 --> 01:15:39.900
Sleep away your sorrow

01:15:40.637 --> 01:15:43.467
He shouldn't do things like that
on a night like this. Good night.

01:15:43.567 --> 01:15:46.900
May make us forlorn

01:15:47.358 --> 01:15:50.392
But with the dawn

01:15:50.687 --> 01:15:53.258
A new day is born

01:15:53.358 --> 01:15:58.133
So I'll say good night,
sweetheart

01:15:58.688 --> 01:16:02.332
Though I'm not beside you

01:16:02.912 --> 01:16:05.694
Good night, sweetheart

01:16:06.176 --> 01:16:09.788
Still my love will guide you

01:16:10.241 --> 01:16:13.023
Dreams enfold you

01:16:13.440 --> 01:16:17.215
In each one I'll hold you

01:16:17.697 --> 01:16:20.599
Good night, sweetheart

01:16:20.705 --> 01:16:22.623
Good night

01:16:24.993 --> 01:16:28.027
Good night, sweetheart

01:16:28.513 --> 01:16:31.993
Till we meet tomorrow

01:16:32.673 --> 01:16:35.674
Good night, sweetheart

01:16:35.906 --> 01:16:39.419
Sleep away your sorrow

01:16:40.194 --> 01:16:45.944
Tears and partings
may make us forlorn

01:16:47.074 --> 01:16:49.921
But with the dawn

01:16:50.178 --> 01:16:53.099
A new day is born

01:16:53.199 --> 01:16:57.824
So I'll say good night,
sweetheart

01:16:58.371 --> 01:17:02.364
Though I'm not beside you

01:17:02.467 --> 01:17:04.988
Good night, sweetheart

01:17:05.604 --> 01:17:09.532
Still my love will guide you

01:17:10.179 --> 01:17:12.896
Dreams enfold you

01:17:13.092 --> 01:17:16.954
In each one I'll hold you

01:17:17.220 --> 01:17:20.067
Good night, sweetheart

01:17:20.196 --> 01:17:22.115
Good night

01:17:24.389 --> 01:17:28.000
Good night, sweetheart

01:17:28.101 --> 01:17:32.029
Till we meet tomorrow

01:17:32.293 --> 01:17:35.108
Good night, sweetheart

01:17:35.461 --> 01:17:39.072
Sleep will banish sorrow

01:17:39.748 --> 01:17:42.578
Tears and parting

01:17:42.678 --> 01:17:45.826
May make us forlorn

01:17:46.565 --> 01:17:48.462
But with the dawn

01:17:48.562 --> 01:17:51.267
I can't open
this blasted dress.

01:17:51.813 --> 01:17:54.661
All right.
Come over here to the light.

01:17:54.822 --> 01:17:57.310
Good night, sweetheart

01:17:57.958 --> 01:18:01.602
Though I'm not beside you

01:18:02.118 --> 01:18:06.511
Good night, sweetheart
Still my love will guide you

01:18:06.611 --> 01:18:07.749
Sorry.

01:18:09.735 --> 01:18:11.248
Dreams enfold you

01:18:11.348 --> 01:18:13.776
Can you get it?
Just a minute.

01:18:13.876 --> 01:18:16.148
In each one I'll hold you

01:18:16.248 --> 01:18:18.355
Oh, darling, darling, darling!

01:18:18.455 --> 01:18:20.447
Good night, sweetheart

01:18:20.584 --> 01:18:22.502
Good night

01:18:25.256 --> 01:18:28.158
I hope you realize
this is costing us millions.

01:18:30.504 --> 01:18:32.422
Good night

01:18:44.489 --> 01:18:46.612
I suppose there's a law
against shooting those things?

01:18:46.712 --> 01:18:48.704
Yes, ma'am, I think there is.

01:18:50.825 --> 01:18:53.607
Oh, good morning, Toto.
Greetings.

01:18:55.848 --> 01:18:57.973
It doesn't seem to matter how
much champagne you soak up,

01:18:58.073 --> 01:18:59.538
you always feel great
the next morning.

01:18:59.638 --> 01:19:01.619
Hello.
Thank you, darling.

01:19:01.719 --> 01:19:04.869
I suppose it takes an iron
constitution to be a house guest.

01:19:13.610 --> 01:19:16.083
Why don't you go away
someplace?

01:19:16.183 --> 01:19:17.909
There must be somebody else
who can use a house guest.

01:19:18.009 --> 01:19:19.572
I can't be
the only sucker in the world.

01:19:19.672 --> 01:19:21.652
Why don't you go to Havana?
That's a nice place,

01:19:21.752 --> 01:19:23.317
and I'd treat you
to a nice one-way ticket.

01:19:23.417 --> 01:19:25.877
Havana? You, me, Havana?

01:19:25.977 --> 01:19:29.379
No, Toto.
You, Havana. Me, here.

01:19:29.484 --> 01:19:31.655
Nitz.
I was afraid of that.

01:19:32.267 --> 01:19:34.584
Say, Maude, is this all right? You
have to work fast in these matters,

01:19:34.684 --> 01:19:36.375
so I just slid down to Margetsons
and slid back with this.

01:19:36.475 --> 01:19:38.868
Hello.
What is it? The Hope Blue?

01:19:38.968 --> 01:19:40.183
No, no, it's just
a chip from it.

01:19:40.283 --> 01:19:42.644
Boy, when you fall,
you fall, don't you?

01:19:42.744 --> 01:19:44.503
Go away, Toto.
This might give you ideas.

01:19:44.603 --> 01:19:45.597
It's all right, then?

01:19:45.697 --> 01:19:47.125
I think she'll know what you mean. Good.

01:19:47.225 --> 01:19:50.069
How do you think this would
look on the Captain's vest?

01:19:50.169 --> 01:19:52.196
Maude,
you're really incorrigible.

01:19:52.748 --> 01:19:55.432
No, no, Toto.
Naughty, naughty. Here.

01:20:28.909 --> 01:20:31.706
I suppose I'll have to give
the bracelet back, won't I?

01:20:31.806 --> 01:20:32.807
Why?

01:20:34.607 --> 01:20:36.037
Oh, dear.

01:20:36.399 --> 01:20:38.341
What are you talking about?

01:20:38.640 --> 01:20:40.633
Snoodles, I'm so fond of you.

01:20:40.733 --> 01:20:42.589
You're a lovely, generous,
good-hearted man.

01:20:42.689 --> 01:20:45.404
Really a woman's ideal. Only, you
shouldn't have sung last night.

01:20:45.504 --> 01:20:46.936
What?
Here's your bracelet.

01:20:47.036 --> 01:20:48.413
I'm going back to my husband.

01:20:48.513 --> 01:20:50.041
That skunk?
Oh, he isn't really.

01:20:50.141 --> 01:20:52.121
I let you think much worse
about him than he is.

01:20:52.221 --> 01:20:53.688
You know how a woman
likes sympathy.

01:20:53.788 --> 01:20:55.256
But what about the $99,000?

01:20:55.356 --> 01:20:57.467
He didn't want that,
I wanted it for him.

01:20:57.567 --> 01:20:58.704
But...

01:21:00.785 --> 01:21:02.201
Put it away.
What?

01:21:02.301 --> 01:21:04.111
Put it away.
But, darling...

01:21:04.273 --> 01:21:06.908
I'll just take one more look at
it and then put it away forever.

01:21:07.008 --> 01:21:09.808
There's a limit
to what a woman can stand.

01:21:11.281 --> 01:21:13.404
Hello there, Snoodles.
How's every little thing?

01:21:13.504 --> 01:21:15.741
I'm very unhappy, as a matter
of fact. You'll get over it.

01:21:15.841 --> 01:21:17.403
You know about Gerry's decision? Yes.

01:21:17.503 --> 01:21:20.572
I'll never get over it as long as I
live. I had such hopes, such plans.

01:21:20.672 --> 01:21:22.651
Oh, Snoodles, I'm so sorry.

01:21:22.751 --> 01:21:25.022
Anyway, we still have the
airport, that'll keep us busy.

01:21:25.122 --> 01:21:27.935
What's knittin', kittens?
Gerry's going back to her husband.

01:21:28.035 --> 01:21:30.367
Oh, you poor dumb thing.
I know just how it is.

01:21:30.467 --> 01:21:31.645
I'll bet he's a knockout.

01:21:31.745 --> 01:21:33.054
I'm awfully sorry
about Snoodles.

01:21:33.154 --> 01:21:35.007
Well, anyway, darling, you'll
still have your airport,

01:21:35.107 --> 01:21:37.790
and you and the Captain and I will be
as busy as bird dogs, won't we, Captain?

01:21:37.890 --> 01:21:39.549
I'm afraid that isn't
possible, either. Why not?

01:21:39.649 --> 01:21:42.366
I still have, I always will have
the deepest affection for you.

01:21:42.466 --> 01:21:44.799
Certainly nothing has happened to
spoil my friendship with your brother.

01:21:44.900 --> 01:21:46.300
Being with him
will remind me of you.

01:21:46.400 --> 01:21:48.460
Well, you see...
What now?

01:21:48.819 --> 01:21:50.975
He isn't exactly my brother.

01:21:51.075 --> 01:21:53.548
He isn't exactly your brother?
No.

01:21:53.747 --> 01:21:56.464
Hello.
Oh, shut up.

01:21:56.595 --> 01:21:58.945
He's my husband.

01:21:59.045 --> 01:22:00.606
He's your husband?
That's right.

01:22:00.706 --> 01:22:03.677
Well, no wonder. I thought
I was losing my grip.

01:22:03.777 --> 01:22:05.503
You mean the vermin who...
Who... Who... Who what?

01:22:05.603 --> 01:22:07.678
That's right, you said he
didn't. Then who is McGlue?

01:22:07.778 --> 01:22:09.888
There is no McGlue. Well,
thank heavens for something.

01:22:09.988 --> 01:22:10.980
That name.

01:22:11.080 --> 01:22:12.639
Then it's the Jeffers Airport.
That's it, isn't it?

01:22:12.739 --> 01:22:14.141
Are you still talking
about that airport?

01:22:14.241 --> 01:22:16.157
You really take it on the
chin, don't you? Why not?

01:22:16.257 --> 01:22:17.984
If an idea has merit,
it has merit.

01:22:18.084 --> 01:22:19.965
Sentiment and business
don't belong in the same bed.

01:22:20.065 --> 01:22:23.038
After all, Grandfather loathed oil.
You know it made his eyes water.

01:22:23.138 --> 01:22:24.800
But that didn't stop him from
making millions out of it.

01:22:24.900 --> 01:22:26.845
You mean you still want to
go through with the airport?

01:22:26.945 --> 01:22:29.056
Why not? On a purely
business basis, of course.

01:22:29.156 --> 01:22:31.808
Right now I don't like you,
although I may get over it later.

01:22:31.908 --> 01:22:33.919
Right now I need something
to occupy my mind.

01:22:34.019 --> 01:22:37.056
The airport is something, if
not exactly what I hoped for.

01:22:37.156 --> 01:22:39.134
I'll be very lonely
without you, Gerry.

01:22:39.234 --> 01:22:41.150
Oh, Captain, and thou.

01:22:41.250 --> 01:22:43.393
I don't suppose
you have a sister?

01:22:43.493 --> 01:22:44.926
Only a twin sister.

01:22:45.026 --> 01:22:47.422
A twin sister? Oh, didn't
you know about that?

01:22:47.522 --> 01:22:50.080
That's how we were married in
the beginning, both being twins.

01:22:50.180 --> 01:22:51.555
Of course that's another plot
entirely.

01:22:51.655 --> 01:22:53.086
Both twins?
Both twins?

01:22:53.186 --> 01:22:54.271
Are you a twin?
Are you a twin?

01:22:54.371 --> 01:22:55.345
Yes.

01:22:55.445 --> 01:22:56.738
Well, what's he doing?
Well, what's she doing?

01:22:56.840 --> 01:22:58.384
Well, nothing.
Well, nothing, you see...

